text:
수많은 미투 속에서 그 첫 신호를 쏘아올린 서지현 검사의 근황이라고 합니다.

요약
서검사는 아직 정상근무를 하지 못함
동기 대부분과 서검사도 부부장으로 승진했으나 언론이 엄청난 승진을 한 것처럼 부풀려 보도함
폭로이후 2차가해를 주도한 사람들이 검찰에서 큰 보직으로 승진함
서검사는 이것을 검찰이 주는 메시지라고 합니다. "너는 우리 조직의 명예를 더럽혔다"

라는 메세지겠지요.

마치 인도같은 곳에서 여성이 강간을 당했을 때 
가정에서 더럽혀진 여자취급을 하면서 죽이는 것과 비슷하지 않나요?

학교에서도 많이들 그러지 않습니까
무슨 일이 있었을 때 "괜히 소문 안좋아지니까 우리 선에서 해결하자
이거 알려지면 우리한테도 좋을거없다"

이것은 누구를 위한 말일까요.

수많은 피해자들이 이를 이유로 일상으로 돌아가지 못하고 있습니다.

안태근 사건은 끝나지 않았습니다.

#미투 #미투운동 #위드유 #서지현 #안태근 #검찰 #검찰내성폭력 #성범죄 #성범죄폭로 #2차가해 #역고소 #무고 #무죄 #근황 #검사 #방관자들 #metoo #withyou

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the start.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing for the 2016 election.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the content and more or less fake accounts - there is no way they are going to their business by taking the responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole thing is build on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing for the 2016 election.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the content and more or less fake accounts - there is no way they are going to their business by taking the responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole thing is build on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text_retweet:
sometimes it feels like, i just wanna rip it out to make my chest stop aching! 
sometimes the pain is so overwhelming  you forget all the tricks of the trade to real you back in. 
and of course there are those times when all you want to do is crawl in bed, pull the covers over your head and scream! which i recommend everyone doing once in a while, it clears you out & does help you feel a little release. 
grief, loss, broken-hearted, it is all related to the same hopeless, guilt ridden, shameful emotional, feelings of overwhelming proportions-in which you can temporarily loose your mind, heart & soul. 
it’s ok, to break apart, as long as you don’t stay there....because the pain will settle in your body and create more resistance, more illness and more days of thunder. movement to ease the pain in the body so the mind can focus on healing...this is my medicine, my therapy, my salvation!

text:
"always get consent"

tw: rape culture

part of an upcoming series that addresses what i feel are common misconceptions regarding #rapeculture.
 i believe there is a need to challenge the existing stereotypes about the victims and perpetrators of sexual violence. in my opinion (you might  disagree) some people disregard the significance of consent and fail to understand the concept of rape. this is my attempt to rewrite the current rhetoric regarding this topic and make it more inclusive and comprehensive. hopefully, i can use my art to raise awareness about sexual harassment, assault and abuse, because i personally feel these are extremely important problems that must be addressed and discussed extensively in order to reach some some kind of solution
#artagainstabuse

if anyone has any ideas for improvement or or feels that i've left something out, please dm me. i believe that everyone can make a positive contribution to this cause. 
as part of the community, it is our job to help raise awareness about serious issues and work together in order to achieve a common goal.

i understand some people might find this offensive and obviously you have a right to an opinion but please refrain from being disrespectful and saying hateful things. i have my views and you have yours, lets just leave it at that :)
.
.
.
.

#metoo #metoopakistan #metoomovement

 i believe there is a need to challenge the existing stereotypes about the victims and perpetrators of sexual violence. in my opinion (you might  disagree) some people disregard the significance of consent and fail to understand the concept of rape. this is my attempt to rewrite the current rhetoric regarding this topic and make it more inclusive and comprehensive. hopefully, i can use my art to raise awareness about sexual harassment, assault and abuse, because i personally feel these are extremely important problems that must be addressed and discussed extensively in order to reach some some kind of solution
#artagainstabuse

if anyone has any ideas for improvement or or feels that i have left something out, please dm me. i believe that everyone can make a positive contribution to this cause. 
as part of the community, it is our job to help raise awareness about serious issues and work together in order to achieve a common goal.

i understand some people might find this offensive and obviously you have a right to an opinion but please refrain from being disrespectful and saying hateful things. i have my views and you have yours, lets just leave it at that :)
.
.
.
.

#metoo #metoopakistan #metoomovement

text:
tw: sexual assault

the weight of wordlessness

what is an invitation?
is it a meaningful look at a chance encounter?
a sudden accidental touch as we pass each other by?
is it in the weight of your gaze, the scorching heat in your eyes as they burn with intent?
or in the pressure of your calloused fingers as they move across my skin?
is it in the frantic pounding of my heart?
 in the blood boiling in my veins?
or in the sudden spastic tightening of my fists as your hands begin to move lower and lower?
or maybe this is enough?
my stuttering breaths, muffled into soft cotton as your lips gently graze my hair
my pliant, boneless limbs shaking as your fingers trace the curvature of my spine
my tongue-tied passivity as your hands mold themselves around my waist
maybe my silence is all the invitation you'll ever need.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
#metoomovement #metoo #metoopakistan #consent #sexualabuse #sexualassault

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text:
#day27 #inktober2018 #thunder 
this is my version of indra, the god of thunder. he rides atop airavat, the white elephant who has five trunks and as many tusks. his weapon is the lightning bolt. as the story goes, he was amorous by nature and deceptive to boot, prone to eying every woman he came across. one such misadventure by deception with the beautiful wife of sage gautama, ahalya, caused him to be cursed with a thousand vaginas all over his body to constantly shame him for his uncontrollable amorous advances. unable to bear the shame he requested the sage to take back his curse. gautama then converts the vaginas to eyes, which remain all over indra's body.

잠실고, 일신여상, 일신여중 서울학원재단이 운영하는 학교들에서 미투 진행중입니다. 민원 의사 있으신 분들 함께 했으면 해서 가져왔습니다.
.
.
더불어
정발고 2차 가해와 피해자들까지 까발려져서 공개적으로 공격받고 있다고 들었습니다.
신송중은 학생들이 계속 공개사과 요구중이구요.
민원 외에도 트위터 있으신 분들은 리트윗과 트윗으로 총공 참여하여 목소리 함께 높여 연대 가능한 것으로 알고 있습니다.
.
.
서울학원재단,정발고,신송중 민원, 총공에 연대 함께 갔으면 좋겠습니다~
.
.
. • • • • •
트위터 제보글 공론화 목적으로 인스타그램 계정을 만들었습니다. 서울학원재단 학생들의 미투에 귀기울여주시고 연대해주세요.
#미투 #미투운동 #metoo #서울학원재단 #서울학원재단_성폭력고발 #잠실여고_미투 #일신여중_미투 #일신여상_미투 #서울학원재단_미투 #스쿨미투

text:
driving in saudi arabia 💃🚘. only in june 2018, women were allowed to drive in saudi. so many atrocities were said when the permit was released: "we'll see more accidents because they don't know how to drive", "it will raise the unemployment as the drivers will have no job anymore", "they'll distract the other drivers around" and many others that are not worthy to mention. unfortunately i've been here for 3 months and i haven't seen a single women driving yet. it's not an easy country to drive though, but i hope to see more women driving here soon.
#braziliandrivinginksa
.
dirigindo na arábia saudita 💃🚘.
somente em junho de 2018, as mulheres conseguiram permissão para conduzir na arábia saudita. tantas atrocidades foram ditas quando a permissão foi liberada: "vamos ver mais acidentes porque elas não sabem dirigir", "isso aumentará o desemprego, já que os motoristas não terão mais trabalho", "elas vão distrair os outros motoristas" e muitas outras que não são dignas de menção. infelizmente, estou aqui há 3 meses e ainda não vi nenhuma mulher dirigindo. não é um país fácil para conduzir, mas espero ver mais mulheres dirigindo aqui em breve.
#womenrightsaroundtheworld

text: jag tycker man ska totalt strunta i att det finns några (förmodligen många) som inte tycker att dom är offer eller mår dåligt av att spela in porr eller sälja sex. jag säljer ju sex själv och jag ”känner” inte att det är värre än att sköta om ett bensår eller torka någon i rumpan på ett vårdhem. det relevanta är att porr kan förstås med sociologisk inlärningsteori. porr lär in ett destruktivt sexuellt beteende som förvirrar sexualitet och förvärrar/lär ut perversioner som i sin tur normaliseras när ”kvinnan i porrfilmen log ju när 13 män hade analsex med henne och pissade henne i munnen”. porr tänjer på gränserna och gör det förbjudna mindre tabu. porr sexualiserar barnkroppar och ”teens”. porr sexualiserar incest med kategorier som ”daddy”, ”stepmom”, ”sister” osv. porr normaliserar halsknull, kiss i mun och ansikte, att dricka sperma eller äta bajs. det finns en kategori porr som kallas ”refugee porn”, alltså porr med flyktingar som då ofta är våldtäktstema. porrskådisar som ”tjänar massa pengar” vinner ingenting på att dessa våldsamma, förtryckande, maktstrukturer upprätthålls och cementeras. alla världens kvinnor drabbas av vad män sett i porr. alla världens horor som säljer sex måste göra det män sett i porr. och vi som då går med på detta sk ”sex” är väldigt många världen över. igår skammades jag för att jag tar för lite pengar, och att det är det som är problemet och inte att män köper sex eller ägnar sig åt våldsporrsex. jag skammades av en ”sexarbetare” som påstod sig tjäna 50 tusen per jobb. som kunde sålla bland erbjudanden och lyckats klassresa upp pga att ha sålt sin kropp utan att någon ”gubbe rört henne”. men guess what?! ska vi inte ta och fråga en missbrukare eller en papperslös eller nån som t.ex rosenlundsstödet möter hur många kronor dom/(vi) får? dom flesta av oss i prostitution försöker bara få ekonomisk grundtrygghet. mat, bostad, kläder - i vissa fall knark. varken porr eller prostitution är något som nån annan är patriarkatet vinner på. gillar man förtryck amen va en rövslickare åt patriarkatet då. själv hatar jag varenda mansjävel som sticker åt mig ett par hundra för att slicka röv. #prostitution #utanskyddsnät #metoo #intedinhora

text:
“driving and sex are both privileges granted at certain ages, both can do irreparable damage when done recklessly, but only driving requires tests, checkpoints and licences.” ... literally smashed this book out in 3 days - i could not put it down. i’ve taken a considerable interest this year in educating myself through various books/essays on the blurred lines around consent, sexual assault and the injustices faced by women (and children) who have chosen to confront a system that unfortunately, yet continuously works against them. i think everyone should - equal rights, feminism, #metoo - this is all part of a larger movement building momentum, where uneducated opinions can have horrendous consequences. i was appalled page after page at the anecdotes bri tells through her time as a judges associate, as well as at the arrogant attitude of her own abuser when forced to be held accountable - but the strength bri holds to weave such a delicate narrative in with a raw, unfettered insight into her life is to be admired and applauded. incredible 🙌🏼 @bri.e.lee .

text: last week i got to speak st @mediacomuk on a panel about the black community and mental health. it was amazing to speak on something that’s affected me so much since i was a child. when i was a child, struggling to recover from being molested, i didn’t know my mental health was extremely damaged. when i struggled with sexuality & self esteem for a decade and a half i didn’t know why. i thought the abuse was my fault. when i turned to porn and became addicted, i felt dirty and wracked with guilt. i didn’t understand then that these were all painful side effects of 5 years of abuse. but then i met a man named jesus. and my life has never been the same. i used to walk past this building on my way to a call centre job i hated 😒😒 that helped fund my youtube channel. now i’m speaking there! dad(god) has an incredible sense of humour! 😂🙌🏾🙌🏾 “tell the godly that all will be well for them. they will enjoy the rich reward they have earned!” isaiah 3:10

text:
en annan grej vi kvinnor bör sluta upp med är att förminska sexism och övergrepp. har på allvar mött flertalet kvinnor som resonerat ”jag blev ju i alla fall inte våldtagen”😰👿 ... att börja se de sjuka strukturerna är ett måste om vi ska få, skapa ett bättre samhälle för våra barn. att bli utsatt, att vara ett offer för systematiska patriarkala kränkningar är inte ett jävla misslyckande som man med näbbar och klor måste försöka vifta bort, vara ”starkare än att ta åt sig av”. herregud, att alldeles för många pojkar och män tamefan överallt kränker flickor och kvinnors integritet och tar sig friheter med våra kroppar - där har vi det stora, skämmiga misslyckandet. 
och nej, det är ingen ”nyttig lärdom” eller att ”lära sig spelets regler” att vara ung tjej som blir tafsad på av sina manliga kollegor. det är enbart övergrepp som bör polisanmälas. sexistisk jargong är inget man bör kunna ”ta”. och systerskap handlar om att se det och stå upp för det. oavsett hur lite man själv vill kalla sig offer, oavsett om man envisas med att reducera det man själv varit med om till ”lite knasigt”.

text:
hallo ihr lieben! ❤️
ich werde nun wirklich mal versuchen meine geschichte in worte zu fassen.. tut mir jetzt schon mal leid, wenn das nicht das beste sein wird, was ihr jemals gelesen habt, aber ich bin nicht so gut in gefühle zugeben und der gleichen. ich muss auch leider ein tw davor setzen. da meine geschichte ein wenig länger wird, teile ich das auf.. der erste teil wird sich um meine psychischen krankheiten drehen und die andern werdet ihr dann ja auch noch sehen.. vielleicht mach ich auch zwei zu meiner psyche, ich muss mal schauen. so jetzt aber...
wann alles so genau angefangen hat ist schwer zu sagen, vielleicht mit 9. ich hatte teilweise richtig starke  angstzustände und hab verweigert zu schlafen, da ich so große angst hatte alleine zu sein.. mit 11/12 hab ich dann angefangen an mir zu zweifeln.. ich hab mich einfach unglaublich unwohl in mir gefühlt und bin einfach nicht wirklich zurecht gekommen mit mir selber.. da ging es mir dann eben phasenweise gut und dann wieder schlecht, aber im großen und ganzem war es ertragbar. richtig schlimm wurde es, als ich mit 13 meine erste richtige beziehung hatte.. der junge hat mir all mein übriges selbstbewusstsein gestohlen und mich leider auch genötigt und sexuell missbraucht... das hat mir dann den rest gegeben und meine psyche ging endgültig den bach runter, ich hab mich selbst verletzt, bin in diverse esstörungen hinein gerutscht und hatte phasenweise sehr mit depressionen zu kämpfen. aber auch das war zeitweise alles besser.. fragt mich nich wie, aber ich habe es irgendwie geschafft, dass meine eltern nichts davon mitbekommen haben... naja mittlerweile hat sich noch mal einiges verändert, aber dazu in einem anderen post mehr. wenn ihr fragen habt, dann fühlt euch frei sie mir zu stellen! auch gerne irgendwelche generellen fragen! ganz viel liebe an euch! ❤️ #löwenkämpfer #strongertogether #staystrong #metoo #mentalillness #storyofmylife #ed #depressionsucks #fighter

text:
'dussehra' is the occasion of rise of good over evil. centuries changes. new generation struggles to find cause and place of these occasions in their lives. ours generation is full of evils. intolerance, climate change, poverty, hunger. oppression, rapes, mob lynchings and political immorality. cyber crimes, obesity and cancers. unemployment and religious bigotry. unwise use of technology, filthy and mounting sewage in the cities and junk infrastructure. i think we indians are in the age of transformation. i - you - we and society all have evils within us and outside. let's identify and accept the existence of evils without hesitation. let's understand the strength of good to win over that evil. let's pledge to wipe out every sin of our generation. let's celebrate this dussehra with collective ambitions, innocent love and social harmony.
caption: ganesh deshmukh

text:
in life, your self-belief will be under constant assault from the outside. - true growth, and the journey to unconditional self-acceptance, begins on the inside, though.
.
@themindshiftacademy i’ve walked through the fire. i’ve been emotionally burned, scarred and rebuilt from within. and now... i know my truth, i live my truth and i project my truth.
—> the result? people are magnetically drawn to my inner strength... like a moth to the flame.
.
realizing my true worth was like being born again. i felt transformed. recreated. alive.
.
i’ve now made it my mission to serve those of you are are tired.. stressed.. lost.. hurt.. emotionally burned.. scared.. fearful... .. there are proven steps, based on neuroscience, positive psychology, and emotional intelligence, that i took to fully transform myself. but it took me years of self-help to figure out the exact steps which triggered the most incredibly powerful shift of my life.
... i’ve put this together into an incredibly high impact, 12 week 1:1 coaching program called.. “build unbreakable self-belief” or b.u.s. 🚌 .
.
stop waiting for someone or something to heal you.. i’ll guide you through the steps to gain such insane clarity on who you are, what you stand for and what you are and are not willing to accept in your life that your mindset will be shifted forever.
.
👉click email above and reach out for a complimentary 20 mins discussion right now. it’s your time now. this is all about you 💕

are you ready to become your own greatest fan? .
.

text:
ಯಾರನ್ನೂ ಡಿಫೇಮ್‌ ಮಾಡೋದಕ್ಕೆ #metoo ಪೋಸ್ಟ್‌ ಮಾಡಿಲ್ಲ: ಸಂಗೀತಾ ಭಟ್​​ ಸ್ಪಷ್ಟನೆ

ತನಗೂ #metoo ಅನುಭವವಾಗಿತ್ತು ಎಂದು ಕೆಲವು ದಿನಗಳ ಹಿಂದೆ ನಟಿ ಸಂಗೀತಾ ಭಟ್‌ ಹೇಳಿಕೊಂಡಿದ್ದರು. ಸಂಗೀತಾ ಭಟ್ ಯಾರ​​ನ್ನೂ ಹೆಸರಿಸದೇ ಫೇಸ್​​ಬುಕ್​​​ನಲ್ಲಿ ಪೋಸ್ಟ್​ ಹಾಕೋ ಮೂಲಕ ತನ್ನ ಮೇಲೆ ದೌರ್ಜನ್ಯ ನಡೆದಿತ್ತು ಎಂದಿದ್ದರು. ಸಂಗೀತಾ ಭಟ್​​ ಆರೋಪದ ಹಿನ್ನೆಲೆಯಲ್ಲಿ ಸಾಮಾಜಿಕ ಜಾಲತಾಣದಲ್ಲಿ ಪ್ರಖ್ಯಾತ ನಟರೊಬ್ಬರ ಹೆಸರು ಕೇಳಿಬಂದಿತ್ತು. ಈ ಹಿನ್ನೆಲೆಯಲ್ಲಿ ಖುದ್ದು ನಟಿ ಸಂಗೀತಾ ಭಟ್‌ ಸ್ಪಷ್ಟನೆ ನೀಡಿದ್ದಾರೆ. ನನ್ನ ಜೀವನದ ಕೆಟ್ಟ ಅನುಭವವನ್ನು ಹಂಚಿಕೊಂಡಿದ್ದೇನೆ ಹೊರತು ಯಾರೋ ಒಬ್ಬರ ಹೆಸರನ್ನು ನಾನು ಹೇಳಿಲ್ಲ. ಯಾರ ಫೇಮನ್ನೂ ನಾನು ಡಿಫೇಮ್‌ ಮಾಡೋದಕ್ಕಾಗಲಿ ಪೋಸ್ಟ್‌ ಮಾಡಿಲ್ಲ. ನಾನು ಈಗಾಗಲೇ ಫಿಲ್ಮ್‌ ಇಂಡಸ್ಟ್ರಿಯಿಂದ ದೂರವಾಗಿ ಒಂದು ವರ್ಷ ಆಯಿತು. ದಯವಿಟ್ಟು ನನ್ನನ್ನ ನನ್ನಷ್ಟಕ್ಕೆ ಬಿಟ್ಟುಬಿಡಿ. ದಯವಿಟ್ಟು ಯಾರೂ ನನಗೆ ತೊಂದರೆ ಕೊಡಬೇಡಿ ಅಂತಾ ಸ್ಪಷ್ಟನೆ ಕೊಟ್ಟಿದ್ದಾರೆ. ಅನಾವಶ್ಯಕವಾಗಿ ನನ್ನ ಹೆಸರು ಬರ್ತಿದೆ. ನಾನು ನನ್ನ ಪೋಸ್ಟ್​​ನಲ್ಲಿ ಯಾರ ಹೆಸರನ್ನೂ ಪ್ರಸ್ತಾಪ ಮಾಡಿಲ್ಲ. ನೀವು ಏನೇನೋ ಕಲ್ಪಿಸಿಕೊಂಡು ನನ್ನ ಮನಸ್ಸನ್ನು ನೋಯಿಸಬೇಡಿ ಪ್ಲೀಸ್‌ ಅಂತಾ ತಮ್ಮ ಅಳಲನ್ನು ತೋಡಿಕೊಂಡಿದ್ದಾರೆ.

ತನಗೂ  ಅನುಭವವಾಗಿತ್ತು ಎಂದು ಕೆಲವು ದಿನಗಳ ಹಿಂದೆ ನಟಿ ಸಂಗೀತಾ ಭಟ್‌ ಹೇಳಿಕೊಂಡಿದ್ದರು. ಸಂಗೀತಾ ಭಟ್ ಯಾರ​​ನ್ನೂ ಹೆಸರಿಸದೇ ಫೇಸ್​​ಬುಕ್​​​ನಲ್ಲಿ ಪೋಸ್ಟ್​ ಹಾಕೋ ಮೂಲಕ ತನ್ನ ಮೇಲೆ ದೌರ್ಜನ್ಯ ನಡೆದಿತ್ತು ಎಂದಿದ್ದರು. ಸಂಗೀತಾ ಭಟ್​​ ಆರೋಪದ ಹಿನ್ನೆಲೆಯಲ್ಲಿ ಸಾಮಾಜಿಕ ಜಾಲತಾಣದಲ್ಲಿ ಪ್ರಖ್ಯಾತ ನಟರೊಬ್ಬರ ಹೆಸರು ಕೇಳಿಬಂದಿತ್ತು. ಈ ಹಿನ್ನೆಲೆಯಲ್ಲಿ ಖುದ್ದು ನಟಿ ಸಂಗೀತಾ ಭಟ್‌ ಸ್ಪಷ್ಟನೆ ನೀಡಿದ್ದಾರೆ. ನನ್ನ ಜೀವನದ ಕೆಟ್ಟ ಅನುಭವವನ್ನು ಹಂಚಿಕೊಂಡಿದ್ದೇನೆ ಹೊರತು ಯಾರೋ ಒಬ್ಬರ ಹೆಸರನ್ನು ನಾನು ಹೇಳಿಲ್ಲ. ಯಾರ ಫೇಮನ್ನೂ ನಾನು ಡಿಫೇಮ್‌ ಮಾಡೋದಕ್ಕಾಗಲಿ ಪೋಸ್ಟ್‌ ಮಾಡಿಲ್ಲ. ನಾನು ಈಗಾಗಲೇ ಫಿಲ್ಮ್‌ ಇಂಡಸ್ಟ್ರಿಯಿಂದ ದೂರವಾಗಿ ಒಂದು ವರ್ಷ ಆಯಿತು. ದಯವಿಟ್ಟು ನನ್ನನ್ನ ನನ್ನಷ್ಟಕ್ಕೆ ಬಿಟ್ಟುಬಿಡಿ. ದಯವಿಟ್ಟು ಯಾರೂ ನನಗೆ ತೊಂದರೆ ಕೊಡಬೇಡಿ ಅಂತಾ ಸ್ಪಷ್ಟನೆ ಕೊಟ್ಟಿದ್ದಾರೆ. ಅನಾವಶ್ಯಕವಾಗಿ ನನ್ನ ಹೆಸರು ಬರ್ತಿದೆ. ನಾನು ನನ್ನ ಪೋಸ್ಟ್​​ನಲ್ಲಿ ಯಾರ ಹೆಸರನ್ನೂ ಪ್ರಸ್ತಾಪ ಮಾಡಿಲ್ಲ. ನೀವು ಏನೇನೋ ಕಲ್ಪಿಸಿಕೊಂಡು ನನ್ನ ಮನಸ್ಸನ್ನು ನೋಯಿಸಬೇಡಿ ಪ್ಲೀಸ್‌ ಅಂತಾ ತಮ್ಮ ಅಳಲನ್ನು ತೋಡಿಕೊಂಡಿದ್ದಾರೆ.
stop_filter_tweet: ಯಾರನ್ನೂ ಡಿಫೇಮ್‌ ಮಾಡೋದಕ್ಕೆ ಪೋಸ್ಟ್‌ ಮಾಡಿಲ್ಲ : ಸಂಗೀತಾ ಭಟ್​​ ಸ್ಪಷ್ಟನೆ ತನಗೂ ಅನುಭವವಾಗಿತ್ತು ಎಂದು ಕೆಲವು ದಿನಗಳ ಹಿಂದೆ ನಟಿ ಸಂಗೀತಾ ಭಟ್‌ ಹೇಳಿಕೊಂಡಿದ್ದರು . ಸಂಗೀತಾ ಭಟ್ ಯಾರ​​ನ್ನೂ ಹೆಸರಿಸದೇ ಫೇಸ್​​ಬುಕ್​​​ನಲ್ಲಿ ಪೋಸ್ಟ್​ ಹಾಕೋ ಮೂಲಕ ತನ್ನ ಮೇಲೆ ದೌರ್ಜನ್ಯ ನಡೆದಿತ್ತು ಎಂದಿದ್ದರು . ಸಂಗೀತಾ ಭಟ್​​ ಆರೋಪದ ಹಿನ್ನೆಲೆಯಲ್ಲಿ ಸಾಮಾಜಿಕ ಜಾಲತಾಣದಲ್ಲಿ ಪ್ರಖ್ಯಾತ ನಟರೊಬ್ಬರ ಹೆಸರು ಕೇಳಿಬಂದಿತ್ತು . ಈ ಹಿನ್ನೆಲೆಯಲ್ಲಿ ಖುದ್ದು ನಟಿ ಸಂಗೀತಾ ಭಟ್‌ ಸ್ಪಷ್ಟನೆ ನೀಡಿದ್ದಾರೆ . ನನ್ನ ಜೀವನದ ಕೆಟ್ಟ ಅನುಭವವನ್ನು ಹಂಚಿಕೊಂಡಿದ್ದೇನೆ ಹೊರತು ಯಾರೋ ಒಬ್ಬರ ಹೆಸರನ್ನು ನಾನು ಹೇಳಿಲ್ಲ . ಯಾರ ಫೇಮನ್ನೂ ನಾನು ಡಿಫೇಮ್‌ ಮಾಡೋದಕ್ಕಾಗಲಿ ಪೋಸ್ಟ್‌ ಮಾಡಿಲ್ಲ . ನಾನು ಈಗಾಗಲೇ ಫಿಲ್ಮ್‌ ಇಂಡಸ್ಟ್ರಿಯಿಂದ ದೂರವಾಗಿ ಒಂದು ವರ್ಷ ಆಯಿತು . ದಯವಿಟ್ಟು ನನ್ನನ್ನ ನನ್ನಷ್ಟಕ್ಕೆ ಬಿಟ್ಟುಬಿಡಿ . ದಯವಿಟ್ಟು ಯಾರೂ ನನಗೆ ತೊಂದರೆ ಕೊಡಬೇಡಿ ಅಂತಾ ಸ್ಪಷ್ಟನೆ ಕೊಟ್ಟಿದ್ದಾರೆ . ಅನಾವಶ್ಯಕವಾಗಿ ನನ್ನ ಹೆಸರು ಬರ್ತಿದೆ . ನಾನು ನನ್ನ ಪೋಸ್ಟ್​​ನಲ್ಲಿ ಯಾರ ಹೆಸರನ್ನೂ ಪ್ರಸ್ತಾಪ ಮಾಡಿಲ್ಲ . ನೀವು ಏನೇನೋ ಕಲ್ಪಿಸಿಕೊಂಡು ನನ್ನ ಮನಸ್ಸನ್ನು ನೋಯಿಸಬೇಡಿ ಪ್ಲೀಸ್‌ ಅಂತಾ ತಮ್ಮ ಅಳಲನ್ನು ತೋಡಿಕೊಂಡಿದ್ದಾರೆ .

text:
exposition « woman’s power »,#bandjoun station, #balancetonporc,#metoo,#graine de vie. « balance ton porc?.. »
une « graine de vie -balançoire» revêtue  de feuilles d’or accueille un personnage asexué à tête de cochon. 
rien ne bouge.
une main invisible peut à tout moment troubler cette sereine et confortable immobilité... lancé en octobre 2017  à la suite de l’affaire harvey weinstein,
« balance ton porc », équivalent français de « metoo », incite les femmes à dénoncer anonymement le harcèlement et les violences sexistes, en particulier dans le monde du travail.

sur les réseaux sociaux, les langues se délient.

pourtant, même si des milliers de femmes ont pu libérer leur parole, les inégalités subsistent. les femmes dites des «quartiers populaires" ne bénéficient toujours pas du même haut-parleur: précarité, poids de l’environnement familial, social, culturel, religieux, autant de freins interdisant la transparence et la vérité.

en réaction, certaines voix féminines se sont élevées contre cette démarche.
un collectif de 100 femmes, dont #catherine deneuve, a publié dans le monde une tribune intitulée "nous défendons une liberté d'importuner, indispensable à la liberté sexuelle", estimant que "la drague insistante ou maladroite n'est pas un délit, ni la galanterie une agression machiste".
à leur tour, caroline de haas# et trente autres femmes leur ont répondu vertement.

alors, « balance ton porc ? »... ml viebel

text:
tågen hade slutat gå, och han erbjöd mig att sova hos honom. det var fint att få se hans lägenhet med all musik och grejer. jag trodde att vi skulle sova men det tyckte inte han. men vadå du skämtar, vi är ju liksom vänner(?). inget mer. väl? jag sa nej han sa jo. upprepade gånger. jag tänkte att kanske hade han skickat ut en massa flörtsignaler som jag inte bara totalt missat men dessutom omedvetet sagt 'ja' till? kanske hade jag missförstått hela 'sova över'-grejen, och i så fall fick jag skylla mig själv. och dessutom, skulle jag vägra nu skulle han kanske bli arg? kanske skulle vår vänskap blir helt förstörd? plus att jag skulle få sitta ute på någon trottoarkant hela natten tills nästa dags tåg skulle börja gå. så då sa jag ja. låtsades gilla det tills han somnade.

jag tyckte inte det var någon stor grej. skrattade bort det. berättade aldrig för någon att jag hade känt mig tvingad. inte för att jag skämdes utan för att jag helt enkelt är jäkligt van vid att pleasa andra. det är inbyggt i huvudet att andra män.niskors åsikter, teorier, viljor automatiskt är något att anpassa sig till. så att de ska tycka om, eller åtminstone acceptera, ens existens.

jag förstår nu att det ska inte vara så. får inte vara så.

till alla killar som är emot den våldsstruktur som drabbar mestadels tjejer, kvinnor och ickebinära: supporta oss. visa att ni bryr er. våga stå upp för oss och vägra att gå med i de intrampade fotstegen som trycker ned och ignorerar och tar sönder. våga var med i min kamp att förändra världen till något bättre.

#metoo #change #now
name: あめりー清美 (Amelie Kiyomi) 아멜리 키요미

text:
the very first time i read #forcoloredgirls i was in middle school. i fell in love. pages and pages of words that spoke directly to me. written for me. the women became my friends. some topics i didn’t understand because they were of course way beyond my experience, ...but somehow that  didn’t matter. the poems held me and told me that i mattered. that my blackness was beautiful. that i was #enough. i remember finding strength in the very rhythm of the words when i was in high school, facing the reality that the violence of #rape wasn’t something that happened to other people, but something that had happened to me. #metoo i would carry that book, identifying with #ladyinred, drawing strength from #ladyinyellow, & as i got older, i celebrated and mourned my experiences with lovers. i would use her poetry as theme music for parts of my life experiences. over time those topics in the book , “for colored girls who considered suicide when the rainbow is enuf”
that were once beyond my understanding became clear. 
rest in peace #ntozakeshange thank you thank you thank you #blackwomenwriters #legacy @lifewellnessbk #findyourstrength #healing #self #selfcare

text:
a student from the missouri state university (msu) has been charged for allegedly raping a woman hours after she attended a #metoo rally in springfield over the weekend. according to a report by the , zachary alperin, 22, went to some bars with the victim after the rally ended, and then went to the woman’s room on campus, per the court documents.
in her statement, the victim said that she allowed zachary to sleep in her room but told him not to touch her because she was drunk, the springfield news-leader reported. the woman told police that she fell asleep and woke up to find alperin lying naked on top of her. per the springfield news-leader, the woman “alleged that alperin performed sex acts on her and she pushed him away.”
alperin allegedly confessed to performing sexual acts on the victim, as reported by the springfield news-leader. “i guess i tried to force myself on her, and i feel like such a terrible person for it,” the culprit told police. alperin is currently being held at the greene county jail on a bond of $20,000 following the investigation. he has been charged with second-degree rape and second-degree sodomy.
according to state law, if someone is convicted of rape and sodomy in the second degree, they can incur a maximum imprisonment of seven years, along with fines up to $10,000 for each offence. following the news, organizers of the #metoo rally in springfield expressed their shock at the incident and said that they have been “devastated” by the news. however, they appreciated that the victim mustered the courage to report the rape, a report by said.
“we are devastated. the thought that someone would leave our rally feeling so encouraged, just to be raped a few hours later… it is almost too much,” the organizers wrote in a facebook post, as quoted by nbc news. “if the woman who attended our rally that the article is referring to sees this, please know this: we are so proud of you for your bravery in coming forward. we are so sorry. we believe you. this was not your fault in any way. we are here for you,” it further read.

text: ett litet tips! om man råkar i samspråk med någon som tycker att #metoo är överdrivet, att feminismen gått för långt, att ide’n om kvinnors underordning är trams kan det vara bra att ha fredrika bremerförbundets utmärkta lista över viktiga årtal när det gäller jämställdhet till hands . fredrikabremer.se det handlar om lagstiftning från 1600-talet fram till nu som visar vad kvinnor inte ska ha, inte ska få , inte ska tillåtas göra. och tvärtom, lagstiftarna har fram till 1921  varit män. intressant är att lagen om kvinnans oskuld vid giftermål avskaffades 1921! jag hade ingen aning om att vi haft en sådan lag... kvinnojouren.com har en liknande lista, sträcker sig från 1200-talet.

so he was saying to her “ aurat hu tmhara kam ha ghar ma bethna kam ni hta to ghar ja k bethu yahan ane ki zarurat ni” so i stood up for her and said to him “you cannot talk to her like that” say sorry “we are a family here if you cannot appreciate her atleast be supportive instead of that you are demotivating and insulting her” hearing this she started crying and then all the men there started pointing out that now she is playing the victim card and trying to turn the situation in her favour using her tears 👏🏻👏🏻👏🏻 and she is crying because you supported her you should have let this go and she wouldn’t have made a situation out of it👏🏻👏🏻👏🏻
i wana say to this to everyone 
it is time that we women stand together support each other raise our voices and the best thing is if we realise that helping another woman win, cheering her on, raising voice for her, having her back doesn’t take away your blessings infact the more you give the more you receive 
and iam in no way regretting that i supported her if i face any such situation again my reaction will be the same

#womenempowerment #feminist #metoo #tahleelk #supportingwithrespect #giversspecttakerespect #pakistanistreetstyle #pakistanibloggers

this book has many rave reviews.  as a #hockeymom i’m keen to read it.  at the same time, i am slow to pick up a book that will make me cry. 
do you have books you want to read, yet hesitate, resisting the sadness it will bring?

text:
to every woman who stood up saying #metoo, thank you for showing that courage still prevails over oppression
it takes a great deal to come out of sexual harassment whether it's a single act of eve teasing or an attempt to rape. 
the world looses colour when you see your friend, colleague or boss turn into a sexual predator and yes of course #notallmen but almost every woman said me too and that says a lot. 
besides the struggle wasn't over for the women who came up.
from slut shamming to calling these allegations baseless and publicity stunts you bore it all girl and how!
cheers to the courage and yes 'we're not alone'

text:
africans for accountability (afa) was mobilized in response to the @propublica/@time investigative reporting regarding the @morethanmeorg/@katiemeyler saga in liberia. afa comprises of a group of multidisciplinary professionals including liberians living at home and abroad, as well as people from across the african diaspora.

we are committed to the common cause of justice, accountability, and holistic response across africa. what affects one affects all. we are not safe until all of us are safe. we endeavor to move beyond mere response, only after the fact, to responsive activism and advocacy that ensures adequate standards for each cause we champion.

text:
10.11.18 - @propublica, in collaboration with @time, published a disturbing report that unveiled the sexual scandal at the @morethanmeorg
academy in west point.
・・・
more than me, an american charity, was created to save vulnerable girls in liberia from sexual exploitation. but from the very beginning, girls were being raped by a staff member.

these are a few of the photographs kathleen flynn, co-director of our new documentary film unprotected, captured for the story.

link in bio.

#morethanme #investigativejournalism #liberia #monrovia #propublica
name: Africans for Accountability
tweet_full:
10.11.18 - @propublica, in collaboration with @time, published a disturbing report that unveiled the sexual scandal at the @morethanmeorg
academy in west point.
・・・

this is a channeled message for all, especially the #metoo survivors:

no, your past do not define you. 
yes, it might have left certain scars on you. the salted trail from the tears are still on your face. but your past do not define you.

let it fuel you, not your bitterness. use it to do something different for the world. and it is possible. 
you have free will. you have the power of choice to create your future, in spite of your past. 
let go of the pain and hate. breathe it all out.

breathe in love.

text:
growing up isn’t easy, that’s why it takes so long to do so.
growing up is also very awkward. there are so many influences and thoughts forced upon you, it’s easy to become brainwashed by the “correct way of passage”. to many of the youth and young babes out there. my advice to you is this; stay true to yourself. which may not make a lick of sense rn but trust me. don’t you dare let someone dictate you on what you are suppose to feel and react to certain obstacles or spectacles. you listen to your own rhythm. you tune in on your vibes of others. because i wish i did when i was younger. i was horribly naive and just wanted to fit in. 
and that stole a piece of me i don’t think i will even gain back.
i was brainwashed into thinking “friends” would never dare hurt another friend or use you for their own personal interest.
boy, was i wrong.
as i’m growing older i feel the urge to share my story. you should not feel ashamed of your own story.
in high school my freshman year was horrible. bestowed my trust on another girl who was true to.
she used me to do her own personal bidding and it costed me my virginity. i was raped by her boyfriend’s friend because i was pawn being used to keep his friend “company”. in a shed. on a couch. i lost all faith in humanity. after the upper class man had left me sobbing and alone. i limped home. i never found my pants he forcibly torn off of me and threw into the darkness. i never felt so alone and numb. i had to break into my own bedroom during the middle of the night because i refused to go back to that girls house. i got to my bedroom and just laid there. i was cold and i felt like a piece of my soul was stolen away from my vessel. i was left bloodied and alone. 
flash forward to today.
i still struggle with that experience. i would never wish that on any soul.
i have random memories flare up from it. but my brain whites out the not so much needed reflections. what’s sad is rape culture is so real it’s sickening.
and what needs to change is the “normal”. we need  a new normal. it starts at such a young age. i’ve even raised my daughter if people say “no” it means “no”. end of story. #metoo

text:
...but it's such a small amount ill be fine...or ...i’ve been using them for years and i’m fine... have these thoughts ever crossed your mind cause i hear them occasionally...and my thought is you deserve better!

lets chat about the effects of bioaccumulation. the epa has stated that small amounts of chemicals are not harmful to the body, but what happens when a small amount of chemicals are found in every single product you use and you use these products every single day, every week, every month for the rest your life? 
a small amount of chemicals in your personal care products, hair products, detergents, and cleaning products can add up to big problems and this can put a significant burden on your body. this is called body burden. you feel fine, until one day, you are don’t. chemicals can stay in your body and build up over time. 😱😱 consider this…
•some chemicals accumulate in our bodies over time
•impacts may show up long after exposure
•some chemicals can become harmful or more toxic in combination with other chemicals
•chemicals can have more impact during certain periods of development (womb, infancy, puberty)
•even tiny doses can be very potent 🌱 i know your probably feeling overwhelmed and so did i when i started. good news is the first step is becoming aware of the toxins!
🌱 educate yourself on ingredients and chemicals you should avoid.  you don’t need to replace every single product in your home tomorrow. transitioning to a healthy, plant-based home is lifestyle journey and you can make changes overtime. start by replacing the products that you use the most. 🌱 i was in your shoes 7 years ago..ill hold your hand and walk you through the process. it wont be overwhelming or scary i promise.  #metoo
#ditchthetoxins
credit:yl

text:
meet vrinda rathi, india’s first female cricket umpire!
.
vrinda rathi 29, is a navi-mumbai based fitness trainer, cleared the board of control for cricket in india’s (bcci) level-2 umpiring exam; is all set to become india’s first female cricket umpire and eligible for umpiring in international women’s cricket.
.
while scoring for india during the women’s world cup 2013, she spotted for the first time a woman umpire: new zealand’s kathy cross. it was the moment that inspired her to make a move to umpiring.
.
rathi has played cricket in her college days and she was a medium pacer bowler. she has represented mumbai university for four years.
.

text:
《5w1h of #remetoo》 【when】
when we read a message or statement on social media with the hashtag "#metoo". 【where】
internet especially social media platforms like "twitter", "facebook" and "instagram". 【who】
everybody who wants to reply positively to a person who made a "#metoo" statement. 【why】
to not mentally isolate people who made a "#metoo" statement and to show them that they are not alone. to show them they are understood and supported. to show a third person who reads the "#remetoo" statement that the person who posts a "#metoo" statement has an ally. 【how】
add the hashtag "#remetoo" behind a positive or supportive statement you wrote as an answer to a "#metoo" statement.

please keep the following guidelines in mind:
"do not ask the person who posted a "#metoo" statement for details".
"do not value any "#metoo" statements".
"do not ask "why?" the person made a "#metoo" statement".
"do not make any suggestions or force the person who made a "#metoo" statement".

text:
new delhi: gerakan #metoo hingga saat ini masih heboh di india. banyak kasus pelecehan seksual yang diungkap dan melibatkan para pelaku industri hiburan, termasuk fotografer bernama raja bajaj (rajesh v bajaj), ayah dari sheena bajaj (pemain thapki). dilansir dari bombay times, rabu (24/10/2018), raja bajaj dituduh telah melakukan pelecehan seksual terhadap aktris sonal vengurlekar pada 2012 ketika sonal masih baru di dunia tv.

sonal menceritakan saat itu ia mendapat panggilan audisi oleh raja. namun karena belum bisa berdialog dengan baik, raja mengajaknya ikut kegiatan pemotretannya agar paham dengan profesi aktris yang ingin digelutinya. mereka kemudian datang ke sebuah resort di khopoli.

meski sudah ada seorang gadis yang jadi model, raja tetap meminta sonal ganti baju dan memakai krim khusus agar bentuk payudaranya bagus. raja bahkan mengikutinya hingga ruang ganti dan memakaikan krim itu dengan paksa. selain itu raja juga mendatangi kamar sonal untuk mengajarinya mantra agar cepat terkenal, dan memintanya duduk telanjang di depannya.

raja bajaj membantah tuduhan tersebut. ia menyebut telah menyuruh sonal pulang bersama model yang ternyata tak cocok untuk pemotretannya. tapi sonal menolak. sonal juga satu kamar dengan para kru sehingga tak mungkin para kru tidak menyadari kehadiran raja.

raja juga menuduh manajer resort tersebut yang justru memerasnya dengan kasus ini, termasuk sonal yang mendatangi rumahnya untuk meminta uang sebesar rs3 lakhs, lalu turun menjadi rs1,5 lakhs. .
.
source by : mediyaa
. .
follow : @dunia_india @dunia_india2 .
.
#sheenabajaj #thapki #metoo #tellywood #duniaindia2

text:
new delhi: sheena bajaj mengalami kejadian tak menyenangkan baru-baru ini. ayahnya, raja bajaj, dituduh telah melakukan pelecehan seksual oleh seorang aktris, sonal vengurlekar.
.
.
.
foto kiri : sheena bajaj 
foto kanan : donal vengurlekar .
.
.

sonal menyebut bahwa peristiwa itu terjadi pada 2012 ketika ia masih menjadi pendatang baru di dunia tv. mantan pemain thapki itu lantas memberikan klarifikasi bahwa tuduhan sonal tidak benar. “sonal hanya memeras ayahku demi uang. saat itu dia baru masuk industri hiburan untuk mengejar karier dan mendapatkan uang. jika ayahku melakukan kesalahan, seharusnya dia pergi ke kantor polisi dan melapor. tapi dia memilih menghubungi ibuku dan menceritakan kejadian itu padanya. dia tadinya minta 5 lakhs, lalu mengurangi nominalnya,” jelas sheena bajaj, dilansir dari india-forums, rabu (24/10/2018). kekasih dari aktor rohit purohit (porus) itu menuturkan bahwa ayahnya menolak memberikan uang. namun sonal pergi ke kantor polisi dan akan menutup kasus ini jika diberi uang.

kasus ini muncul menyusul ramainya gerakan #metoo di india. sheena bajaj sendiri menyayangkan orang-orang yang memanfaatkan itu untuk popularitas. “aku setuju dengan gerakan ini. hampir 80% kasus adalah kejadian nyata. tapi bagaimana dengan 20% sisanya, orang yang hanya menggunakan ini untuk popularitas? ketika insiden ini terjadi, tak ada orang yang melihat meski banyak orang di sana. semua mendengar insiden ini tapi tak ada yang menyaksikannya,” ujarnya. .
.
source: mediyaa .
.
follow : @dunia_india @dunia_india2 .

text:
r.i.p. ntozakes shange 
you gave little girls of color a voice. you advocated for #survivors before there were hashtags or trendy causes. you inspired my voice, my creativity. thank you. #ntozakeshange 🌺🌺🌺🌺🌺🌺🌺🌺🌺🌺🌺🌺🌺🌺🌺🌺🌺🌺🌺
“i write for young girls of color, for girls who don’t even exist yet, so that there is something there for them when they arrive.” — #ntozakeshange 🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹🌹
every 3 minutes a woman is beaten 
every five minutes a 
woman is raped/every ten minutes 
a lil girl is molested 
yet i rode the subway today 
i sat next to an old man who 
may have beaten his old wife 
3 minutes ago or 3 days/30 years ago 
he might have sodomized his 
daughter but i sat there 
cuz the young men on the train 
might beat some young women 
later in the day or tomorrow 
i might not shut my door fast 
every 3 minutes it happens 
some woman's innocence 
rushes to her cheeks/pours from her mouth 
like the betsy wetsy dolls have been torn 
apart/their mouths 
menses red & split/every 
three minutes a shoulder 
is jammed through plaster and the oven door/ 
chairs push thru the rib cage/hot water or 
boiling sperm decorate her body 
i rode the subway today & bought a paper from a 
man who might 
have held his old lady onto 
a hot pressing iron/i don't know 
maybe he catches lil girls in the 
park & rips open their behinds 
with steel rods/i can't decide 
what he might have done i only 
know every 3 minutes 
every 5 minutes every 10 minutes/so 
i bought the paper 
looking for the announcement 
the discovery/of the dismembered 
woman's body/the 
victims have not all been 
identified/today they are 
naked and dead/refuse to 
testify/one girl out of 10's not 
coherent/i took the coffee & spit it up/i found an 
announcement/not the woman's 
bloated body in the river/floating 
not the child bleeding in the 
59th street corridor/not the baby 
broken on the floor/ 
there is some concern 
that alleged battered women 
might start to murder their 
husbands & lovers with no 
immediate cause' 
i spit up i vomit i am screaming 
we all have immediate cause 
every 3 minutes 
every 5 minutes 
every 10 minutes 
every day

text:
people always tell me i am a surrealist writer, and perhaps i am, but im reading black, brown, & beige: surrealist writings from africa and the diaspora, which is about black french surrealism, and it now makes sense why the final-draft readers of my book said it was brilliant
.

before i turned it in to random house i sent to a friend a mine, a black american copy editor working and living in paris with her family. she was like, floored; she loved it. my friend james, who lives between america and paris? he was the first reader. loved it
.

all white people? fucking hate it
.

i think i just write about my reality. but, my really brilliant writer friends who have chosen to expatriate to paris think, from this distance, this read of american race is right on target
.

all very interesting
.

and this definition argues that surrealism is an "open realism" discourse on society, and i'm good with that. there is just so much conversation between adoration and rejection i really hoped it wasn't just about race, but with white people everything is about power, so inadvertently about race, the base of which stands on a thread bare fear
.

my life has been like one very long conversation about how "to catch the best light" on black "skin" through a white lens
.

there is no such thing. it's all designed to flat ...unless of course you turn full frontal and pull the lips of your vagina apart because then your skin has dimension, "-- like hally berry in monsters ball, you saw that right? she won an award for that; made her 10 times as famous". the world is perverted, and there is no difference between sexual harrasment and the perversion of racism
.

i don't want to move to paris but i will learn more french just in case
.

and if a white person flags this bc i said vagina, you flagged this because *i said vagina*

text:
🙌🏼🔊 #awesome #thisisamerica #winning #betofortexas #payitforward #howitsdone #vote #makeadifference — los angeles #lakers player #lebronjames donned a #betoorourke hat ahead of his team's matchup with the san antonio spurs on saturday night.
-
in a photo shared by james' team on  saturday evening, the player could be seen wearing a white hat, reading: "#betoforsenate"
-
the show of support for o'rourke arrives as the texas democrat continues to draw national attention as he seeks to unseat incumbent republican sen. ted cruz in the #texas senate race.
-
this is not the first time the athlete has offered the democrat public support, however.
-
in late august, the #nba star praised o'rourke for a video featuring the political candidate defending defense of #nfl players who kneel during the national anthem.
-
in the 4-minute video, o'rourke said he "can think of nothing more american" than the protests, which he said were meant to bring attention to african-americans who are "being killed at a frightening level right now, including by members of law enforcement, without accountability and without justice."
-
at the time, james called the video a "must watch" and saluted the democrat for his "for the candid thoughtful words."
-
#lebron's political statement on saturday also arrives months after showtime announced it would be teaming up with the athlete to produce a documentary series on the role of athletes in america's current cultural climate. -
the series, titled "shut up and dribble," will take "a powerful inside look at the changing role of athletes in our fraught cultural and political environment," the #losangeles times reported.
-
the title is a reference to a comment fox news host laura ingraham made earlier this year, who responded to political statements from james by telling him to "shut up and dribble."
—
#healthcare #metoo #truth #fuckhaters #obama #lgbtq #historyrepeats #racism #immigration #dumptrump #fucktrump #donaldtrump #trump thanks! @sissymarie3232

text:
my response to the national apology on child sexual abuse. victims of criminal child sexual abuse in australia gathered for an emotional national apology on monday, as grief and remembrance replaced partisanship in federal parliament.

i sat in my room in the clinic in burwood on my own not knowing whether to turn on the television or not. not sure whether i could bear to watch it, desperately afraid of the emotions that it would bring up. i did not know whether those emotions would be ones of sadness, anger, grief or desperation at my ongoing illness. i should have been in group therapy at the time but decided that in the end i would watch it and miss group.

prime minister scott morrison led the apology following a recommendation from the landmark royal commission into institutional child sexual abuse, acknowledging that australian society and religious institutions had covered up crimes and not believed victims for generations.

he paid tribute to survivors and advocates who sought recognition and justice and said victims who were no longer alive had deserved protection and respect. “while we can’t be so vain to pretend to answer, we must be so humble to fall before those who were forsaken and beg to them our apology,” mr morrison told a silent house of representatives. https://youwillbearwitness.com/2018/10/28/my-response-to-the-national-apology-on-child-sexual-abuse/ #ptsdawareness #ptsd #doitfordolly #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #emdr #trauma #metoo #youwillbearwitness #erinfado #ptsd #cardinalpell #dissociativeidentitydisorder

text:
here’s what depression can do to your body. people often think of depression as an emotional disorder that only affects your mood and your mind, and while it is a mental health issue, it can affect your body, too.
“depression not only has an emotional component but [it also has] physical aspects like being low energy, fatigue, exhaustion,” says richa bhatia, md, a child and adult psychiatrist and member of the anxiety and depression association of america.
she adds that it’s important to talk about the physical aspects of depression, along with the emotional symptoms, because they both affect your functioning and quality of life, and because physical symptoms might be more obvious to some people. plus, she adds, emotional symptoms might not manifest themselves at the beginning of someone’s experience with depression, and they may be more able to identify, say, a headache than they’re able to pin down a loss of interest in things they used to enjoy. https://youwillbearwitness.com/2018/10/28/heres-what-depression-can-do-to-your-body-2/ #ptsdawareness #ptsd #trauma #peterfox #ptsdsurvivor #ptsdrecovery #emdr #stopracism #stopbullying #stopchildabuse #metoo #youwillbearwitness #erinfado #cardinalpell #dissociativeidentitydisorder #complexptsd

we've kept in the audience q+a with only a few minor edits for legal or quality issues. the show is available on #itunes #spotify and your usual channels,or direct from https://player.whooshkaa.com/episode?id=297539
enjoy!

text:
this evening i finally had the opportunity to review and fill out the absentee ballot i applied for and received in the mail weeks ago (don't worry, i removed the contents of the envelope for this photo!). it's proven to be the easiest method of voting for me, especially with just being released from the hospital and lacking the energy i need to show up in person on november 6th. this eliminates my anxieties and rids my mind and body of the pressure and intimidation factors that go along with making such crucial decisions for our representatives. 
i am a voter because i'm living with a #disability and require adequate healthcare in order to continue to be here.
i am a voter because i'm a woman, and as a white woman, i have a responsibility to stand in solidarity with women of color who are so often excluded from the conversations. #feminism is only feminism if it is intersectional.
i am a voter because i'm a survivor of sexual violence.
i am a voter because i have my sights set on higher education, and it should be an affordable right as opposed to a privilege.
i am a voter because i welcome everyone seeking a better life in america. 
i am a voter because #lgbtqia rights are non-negotiable; love is love, no matter the form it comes in. love is a kaleidoscope that constantly leaves me mesmerized by its ever-changing design. 
i am a voter because #gunreform is a necessary preventative measure for our homicidal society. 
i am a voter because #policebrutality is an abuse of power we still shamefully ignore. 
i am a voter because there is no planet b, and it's our job to protect this earth before we permanently damage our environmental safety.
i am a voter because of many other reasons, but above all of them, i am a voter because it is my civic duty, and i am a human being driven by research/evidence and empathy.

be a part of the change we so desperately need to see in this world, and restore each other's faith in the national community.
💙😊❤️
#midterms #vote #votethemout #election2018 #earlyvoting #absenteeballot #powertothepolls #bluewave #voteprogressive #novemberiscoming #chronicillness #metoo #equality #intersectionality @kimothy.joy

text: it's difficult for us to accept that, when a woman comes forward with a sexual allegation, she is regularly dismissed. we can't help but notice, however, that these women go on to fight for others where no one fought for them. anita hill went on to write about and provide political commentary. christine blasey ford went on to become a professor of psychology. rachel crooks, who accused donald trump of forcibly kissing her, went on to win the democratic primary for an ohio house of representatives seat earlier this year. she is the first trump accuser to get so close to holding public office, which we find super admirable. keep crushing, rachel.

text:
juana valdes’ hanging by is a collection of text-based ceramic tiles that break down a poetic phrase so that each tile presents the viewer with a new message. a collection of her ceramic ‘colored china rags’ approximate household rags but are made from bone china—distinguished from all other porcelain for its whiteness and translucency. in altering the clay “body” through inserting pigment directly into the clay, valdes questions skin color, tones, aging, and gender bias. her work also serves as a way of highlighting and creating the beauty within the object and artifact of labor.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
last december during miami art week, @anthony_spinello and @zoelukov curated the first in a series of alternative art fairs, entitled “fair.” fair., an alternative non-commercial art fair that took place december 7-10, 2017 at brickell city centre, served as a platform for a diverse and multigenerational group of women artists. fair. seeked to address gender inequality in the art world and beyond by providing space for radical women artists to create site-specific interventions in a non-traditional venue.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
fair. was generously supported by swire properties inc, in partnership with the john s. and james l. knight foundation.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
#sweetheartsaturday christine blasey ford. “we witnessed you show up for duty, not as a superhero, but as a fully human woman. you showed us that the new hero — the kind of  heroism called for in this moment — is a woman facing the patriarchy with no weapons other than her voice, her body, and the truth.”
.
“you showed a world of discounted people what courage looks like. you showed us that survival is ongoing and that the journey, while fraught, is also essential. you reminded us that we are neither powerless nor alone because we have the truth. even if we shake: we will tell our stories.”
– excerpt from a love letter to dr. ford by tarana burke, amanda de cadenet, glennon doyle, tracee ellis ross, and america ferrera.
thank you for this beautiful letter. thank you dr. ford. <3
.
#metoo #believewomen #drfordloveletter

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies. 
they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green, author
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies. 
they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green, author
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
do you know that most of my life i walked around feeling misunderstood and wrong? ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
and no matter how hard i tried to explain it, people didn’t understand. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
it was like being a prisoner in my own skin. and i was trapped behind glass and no one could hear me. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
later on in life, i realized that there wasn’t anything wrong with me at all, but no one ever told me how to get out of that box and be seen…⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
they just told me i was stuck. and so the more i tried to get unstuck, the more i was trapped. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
and the harder i struggled the tighter the knots became…⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
and that is why i created shaktibomb for the feminine souls out there who have always felt stuck or trapped in their own skin.  because like me, you are perfect exactly as you are, it’s just that no one could see you in all your beautiful glory. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but i do. and i want you to know that i love you exactly as you are. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
if you’re looking for that space that feels like coming home to your self, then look no further. because i created my corner of the interwebs just for you. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
come check it out and see for yourself.  the link is in my bio 👆 and there’s a free gift for you too... ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
later on in life, i realized that there wasn’t anything wrong with me at all, but no one ever told me how to get out of that box and be seen…⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
new delhi: sheena bajaj mengalami kejadian tak menyenangkan baru-baru ini. ayahnya, raja bajaj, dituduh telah melakukan pelecehan seksual oleh seorang aktris, sonal vengurlekar.
.
.
.
foto kiri : sheena bajaj 
foto kanan : donal vengurlekar .
.
.

sonal menyebut bahwa peristiwa itu terjadi pada 2012 ketika ia masih menjadi pendatang baru di dunia tv. mantan pemain thapki itu lantas memberikan klarifikasi bahwa tuduhan sonal tidak benar. “sonal hanya memeras ayahku demi uang. saat itu dia baru masuk industri hiburan untuk mengejar karier dan mendapatkan uang. jika ayahku melakukan kesalahan, seharusnya dia pergi ke kantor polisi dan melapor. tapi dia memilih menghubungi ibuku dan menceritakan kejadian itu padanya. dia tadinya minta 5 lakhs, lalu mengurangi nominalnya,” jelas sheena bajaj, dilansir dari india-forums, rabu (24/10/2018). kekasih dari aktor rohit purohit (porus) itu menuturkan bahwa ayahnya menolak memberikan uang. namun sonal pergi ke kantor polisi dan akan menutup kasus ini jika diberi uang.

kasus ini muncul menyusul ramainya gerakan #metoo di india. sheena bajaj sendiri menyayangkan orang-orang yang memanfaatkan itu untuk popularitas. “aku setuju dengan gerakan ini. hampir 80% kasus adalah kejadian nyata. tapi bagaimana dengan 20% sisanya, orang yang hanya menggunakan ini untuk popularitas? ketika insiden ini terjadi, tak ada orang yang melihat meski banyak orang di sana. semua mendengar insiden ini tapi tak ada yang menyaksikannya,” ujarnya. .
.
source: mediyaa .
.
follow : @dunia_india @dunia_india2 .

text: still feeling disbelief over this morning’s events.  also feeling intense sadness and anger.  we have to make changes to stop this senseless suffering.  how scary it is that there is nowhere people can go to feel safe.  schools, concerts, places of worship, shopping malls, movie theaters....the list goes on and on.  i celebrate our differences.  i love learning from others who are not like me.  just because someone looks different, talks different, worships different, loves someone different than you do does not make them less than, scary, evil, or dangerous.  we all have our gifts. please be kind to one another.  get to know people - you will find they aren’t that different from you.  to make change happen, we need to vote on november 6th - and double check your ballot to make sure the ones you intend to vote for, you actually do.  #loveoverhate

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf

text:
with the #metoo campaign currently going around, i feel the need to share something. if you are a survivor of childhood sexual abuse, there is something you can do to help you on your journey to heal. 💖

the younique foundation offers a ✨free✨ retreat to survivors of childhood sexual abuse. they don't force younique products on you, they don't even use our products in the makeover and photoshoot because they don't want there to be even an ounce of room for someone to say they have the wrong intentions. this foundation has 1️⃣ purpose, and 1️⃣ purpose only: to help you heal. 🙌🏻 ➡️no business. no sales.⬅️ nothing except opportunities for you to rediscover your self-worth and heal. you are powerful beyond measure. ❤️💪🏻 if you want to know more, please check out www.youniquefoundation.org, where you can read more and apply to attend the retreat or contact me. 
#nomore1in4 #reclaimhope #ibelieveyou

text:
let’s talk mental health!! 🎀💕
.
.
certain times of life make women more vulnerable to mental health issues. the onset of menses and teen years, pregnancy, postpartum, and perimenopause are just a few of the most vulnerable times a in a woman’s life. this is because of the extreme shifts in hormones that occur during these times. women’s mental health is therefore a lifelong pursuit as emotions, symptoms, and experiences change at each stage of life. understanding this can help women prepare for these vulnerable times and acknowledge the life changes that may be affecting their mental health.
.
.

text:
qanon fans are applying this same participatory behavior that we have celebrated in fiction fandom to real-world political drama. and why not? the boundaries between politics and entertainment have been collapsing for years. the entire trump presidency operates like reality tv, completely divorced from any real stakes or substance.

that’s what makes this all so terrifying. do these people really believe that tom hanks and hillary clinton are personally running a massive pedophilia ring? really??? but consider this: trump announced at a rally this week that the farmers being harmed by his stupid trade war had told him “we can take it.” no actual farmers said that to him. we all know that. but it’s a little thing, just part of the story we are all interacting with.

the pulsating heart of the qanon theory is not a lunatic fringe denying the real consequences of a failing presidency. the heart of it is a devoted fan base constructing elaborate theories to make the story more fun and engaging. and if you start from the premise that nothing government does matters, then it’s easy to come along for the ride. there’s no real difference between hillary clinton and the smoke monster. they’re both just characters on the television.

that’s what alarms me most about the growth of qanon. it’s not that these people are unhinged and possibly armed. it’s that we’ve lost the capacity to treat civics, governance, and public affairs as though they have actual stakes with actual consequences. the premise of the trump presidency is that nothing matters, so you should root for your side and heckle the opposing team. he encourages his supporters to treat democrats and journalists like a rival fan base.

david karpf

text: i don’t scream black lives matter or post #metoo to look trendy online to you. i do it because i looked at my child for the first time and knew that i am responsible for who he will become. he will hear my words, see my actions, and he will follow my lead. i’m far from a perfect person or parent, but i know that seeing diversity as a child allowed me to embrace it as an adult. children raised in hateful environments where women are viewed as inferior and minorities are faggots, spics, or coons can turn into adults that become doctors, educators, judges, or politicians - and thus the cycle of violence continues. the white men who shoot up synagogues, schools, and baptist churches were once children, but are now violent killers. the next time you fail to condemn racism or injustice know that a child is watching and will one day live in the wake of the decision you made. • this was longer than intended, but i look at these pictures only seeing how unfair it is that some parents won’t be home with their children tonight because a violent bigot killed them •

text:
அவர்கள் என்னை பலவந்தப்படுத்தி ஊமையாக இருக்கவைத்துவிட்டனர்!!!
.
அவர்கள் வைத்த கன்னிவெடியில் 
சிதறிய ஊமைக்கன்னி நான்!!!
.
கண்ணியம் என பெண்ணியம் போற்றியவர்கள் என்னை கபகளீரம் செய்தனர்!!!
.
கன்னி இவள் ஊமையை உடைத்தேனெனில், இவளின் ஊமை உடல் புசித்த உங்கள் கரங்களும் 
ஒருநாள் உடைபடும்!!!
.
உங்கள் ஊமை விழிகள் பார்க்கும் நாராசப்பார்வை ஒருநாள் பறிபோகும்!!!
.
உங்கள் தலையும் ஒருநாள் தரையில் உருளும்!!!
.
இந்த ஊமையை உல்லாசம் அனுபவித்த உங்கள் ஊணும் உயிரற்றுப்போகும்!!!
.
உங்கள் இச்சை தீர்க்க என்னை எச்சி படுத்திய நாவும் அறுபடும்!!!
.
என் உயிர்வலி பிடுங்கிய உங்கள் உயிரும் ஒருநாள் பிடுங்கப்படும்!!!
.
அன்றுனர்வீர் ஊமையும் உடைபடும் என்று, உங்கள் மொழியும் ஊமையாகும் என்று!!!
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text: you know i have to talk about it.... 🤷🏾‍♀️😴 so we have woah vicky, the catch me outside girl, tracy barbie, and now this... at this point i have to pick a beef with dr.phil... does anyone else notice how he loves to bring young girls with self image issues race specific and all basically disrespecting black people? i don’t know if the man hates women and or people of color.. but anyone seriously focused on mental health and creating public change would not ridicule and expose such obviously unstable children and exploit them for money on national television. i see you @drphil . at the beginning of the day these are children.. i think parents should be scrutinized before anything... how is it against the law to show pictures of children in media in situations of crime but not illegal to blast children all over the internet, tv and whatever media source in the case of obvious mental illness.... i’m just disappointed in what’s happening around us right now. wake up people!!! our community is dying and we’re killing eachother :( #drphil #drphilshow #racist #sexist #predator #dangerzone #whiteprivilege #whitemaleprivilege #blacklivesmatter #community #thebuzz #unpopularopinion #thesmokeroom #mentalhealthawareness #mentalstrength

text_retweet:
💖💖💖💖⁣
⁣
#repost @littleegypt⁣
⁣
forgiving is easier said then done. ⁣
⁣
it’s more of a practice if you ask me.  you can’t  just forgive and forget.  or at least i can’t. ⁣
⁣
every time a bad memory comes up you feel everything for the first time. ⁣
⁣
so forgiveness is a something that i have to work at all the freakin time. ⁣
⁣
when mike passed i was so angry with him.  we had a deal!! ⁣
⁣
we were suppose to grow old together.  we could handle anything life threw at us, as long as we had each other, we would figure out a way to get through it.  we were best friends. we were going to grow old together.  i could see 20 more years down the road easily. ⁣
⁣
you’ll see us as kids on the next slide ➡️ and then over 30 years later. ⁣
⁣
i found myself all alone for the first time in my life.  i had no one that i could share my deepest fears with.  i had to learn to first forgive myself in order to heal. ⁣
⁣
forgive myself for the anger and everything that hides behind that. ⁣
⁣
#meditation helps me a lot!  my morning meditation relaxes me and the afternoon one heals me.  i’m having trouble getting the 2nd one in.  but i’m continuing to work at it. ⁣
⁣
do you or do you know someone that #mediates regularly?  i’d love to hear about your success.⁣
⁣

text: if, instead of focusing on what we are not getting, we focus on what we can give, life immediately begins to feel better. if, instead of focusing on what is missing, we focus on what we can be thankful for, life immediately begins to feel better. it is when we have a sense of entitlement that life begins to drag us down. if we think we are owed something by life and by the people in it, we are doomed to disappointment. nobody owes us anything. when selfishness becomes extreme, we harbor the illusion that we have the right to take what we want even if it means depriving others of what is rightfully theirs. this may be true in relationships, as well, because some people really don't have relationships, they take emotional hostages. if you stop to think about it, for instance, domestic violence is really a hostage situation in which one partner attempts to imprison the other for his own satisfaction. rape is also an act of selfishness because it means taking what is not freely given. any act of coercion is selfishness. not being willing to agree to disagree is an act of selfishness. greed is an act of selfishness. selfishness is the root of all evil. when we rid ourselves of all forms of selfishness, we rid ourselves of evil intent. #quotesforyou #quotes #selfishness #evil #metoo #greed #loving #recovery #mentalhealth #oktosay #blessings #blogpost #karlyletomms karlyletomms.com
name: Karlyle Tomms

text:
a woman who lied about being raped by two men during a college party appeared to roll her eyes in court as one of the victims talked about how the allegations affected his life.⁣
⁣
nikki yovino, 20, of south setauket, new york, was sentenced thursday in bridgeport superior court to three years in prison, with the sentence suspended after she serves one year. yovino pleaded guilty in june to misdemeanor charges of falsely reporting an incident and interfering with police. ⁣
⁣
yovino was attending sacred heart university, in fairfield, conn., when she reported being raped by two school football players in the bathroom at an off-campus party in bridgeport in october 2016. the two men both admitted to having sex with her, but said they encounter was consensual.⁣
⁣
yovino subsequently admitted making up the claims so she wouldn’t lose a potential boyfriend.although the players were never arrested, both of them withdrew from the school while facing possible discipline, and one of them lost his football scholarship.⁣
⁣
source:foxnews.com

text:
halloween (2018) dir. david gordon green
.
.
.
i loved this film. it amped up the violence - which works better in a modern context - and was just as terrifying, if not more terrifying, than the original. jamie lee curtis was fantastic (as anyone could have guessed) and her granddaughter (and her friends) did pretty decently as well. what the film also did was add a subtle feminist/#metoo movement touch to the story (which i doubt would take away from the experience of non-feminists but will add to the experience of feminists). i also appreciated all the little tributes to he first film. 8.5/10 .
.
.
#halloween #halloween2018 #halloween1978 #halloweenreview #theboogeyman #boogeyman #michaelmeyers #lauriestrode #jamieleecurtis

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since the start.

steve bannon left the wh august last year and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit the hijacked party of puppets is obviously just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt with the brave bunch known as gop has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can easily contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this opportunity and messes with the bombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on my bed.

the whole qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that joseph goebbels would have died for. it is obvious that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing for the 2016 election.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are just helpless with the content and more or less fake accounts - there is no way they are going to their business by taking the responsibility.

there is absolutely no way that gop isn't aware of what is going on - after all cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole thing is build on the same user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got from cambridge analytica.

and here comes the best part. trumq is truly playing along with his tweets, gestures and words.

the bigger issue still is that requqlicans are willingly piggybacking this lunacy and abusing the faith of their fellow men while campaigning for the midterms. this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.
