text: if you identify as a feminist, and are not yet vegan, please research carol’s work. i read this book shortly after i turned vegan nearly 2 years ago and today at @vegfestuk i got to hear carol speak! her theories are as relevant now as when this seminal, groundbreaking book was first published nearly 20 years ago. in the era of the #metoo movement the white patriarchy has come under threat and therefore has become particularly anxious to reassert the idea of a macho, masculine man who is encouraged to consume animals and women. i can’t possibly summarise carol’s incredible theory in an instagram post but i can beg you to make the connection. rebel against the patriarchy and go vegan! #theantitrumpdiet #thefutureisfemale #thefutureisvegan #sexualpoliticsofmeat #feminismisveganism

text:
#latinamericanawards2018 #gloriatrevi
#latinamas2018

la celebración de este año de los latin american awards giró en torno a las mujeres quienes tomaron el escenario para rechazar los abusos sexuales y pedir igualdad de género.

uno de los testimonios que más impactó fue el de gloria trevi, quién años atrás fue juzgada duramente por la justicia mexicana y por todos aquellos quienes no quisieron escuchar su verdad.
como ella misma lo señala, fueron 4 años, 8 meses y 8 días encerrada en una prisión por un delito que no cometió y del cual se aprovecharon muchos medios para ocultar otros crimenes.

una mujer que ha demostrado fortaleza para enfrentar varios abusos desde su niñez, que una vez fuera de la carcel tuvo que empezar de menos que cero para recuperar su vida y que hace dos días, en una infinita muestra de valentía, decidió romper el silencio para ayudar a millones de mujeres que, quizá como ella, están pasando por una situación similar.

nos unimos a la consigna que ha volcado las redes sociales en la premiación de los latin american awards: no volver a callar abusos y acosos.
y hacemos hincapié una vez más de la importancia de todos los movimientos sociales que han ayudado a millones de mujeres a no guardar más silencio frente a los abusos de sus agresores.

#niunamenos #niunamas
#noesno #sólosiessi #metoo
#vivasnosqueremos #cuentalo #nosignificano
#tocanaunarespondemostodas #tocanaunatocanatodas
#muertasdejuarez

text:
"forgiveness cannot change the past but it can enlarge the future." ~ paul boese. 
the world owes an apology to the female community for degrading them for years. making a mindset of male superior society, not only in india but in the whole world. it is an unfortunate truth that was being practised. but now, with strong & smart women, even though slowly, it's changing and it should. 
it's important that no gender should use the false accusations card. be it male or female it really destroys the life of an innocent person. in our country of course there are more females coming out with scary truths that they had to face because of some monsters residing in our society. there's a greater rate of females being molested, raped, violently hurt than men though. our society comes with a lot of problems and mindsets that they have been asked to believe. 
if more men are not coming out in the #metoo movement it's because they're afraid of the society itself because judgement starts from the society. education plays a major factor here but unfortunately our education system didn't believe in teaching the character qualifications but wanted more doctors and engineers. it's a connected viscous cycle. 
it all starts from the roots of a evil idea followed by misunderstandings, building false religious beliefs, politics & the media. 
after some men have built a disgraceful reputation by doing disgusting things in the world people who have suffered have every right to be at least heard. the problem is after the stories are shared. the most rational thing to do is listen and not give the verdict but most people get influenced by the media, surroundings or some random source and start giving out judgements about the right & wrong. where the cases show lack of statements from the accused we can rationalize it down to the truth but it's not true for some of the cases. false accusations win during such time, completely tearing apart the life of the accused be it male or female. 
#metoo #genderequality

text:
happy halloween weekend!
🧙🏼‍♀️✨
here is an excerpt from “evrynome- a story of creation”
by christine lavadas
📖
...she danced and she danced.
.
and from the arch of her foot leapt circles of time
.
and from the curve of her spine, the spirals of life,
.
day and night,
black and white,
absorption, reflection,
death, birth, and resurrection.
.
and as ecstasy grew, as the heat increased, the wind blew wild and her belly swelled round.
.
and from the rivers of her sweat oceans flowed, and with each heave of her breasts, mountains rose.
.
and when she threw back her hair and opened her hands, life teamed around her and harmony reigned.
.
creation now danced in her perfect time
and she smiled.
🌊🌙💃🏼🌎
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
#🇺🇸 ana juan’s “#unheard” #metoo
the #artist #anajuan began contributing to #thenewyorker in 1995, and has since done dozens of covers for the #magazine. 
her cover for next week’s issue draws on the testimony of #christineblaseyford, who on thursday appeared in front of the #senatejudiciarycommittee, to recount her allegation that, in 1982, she was sexually assaulted by the #supremecourt nominee #brettkavanaugh, which he has denied.
(“she speaks for the women who have no voice,” juan says.) for more coverage of the hearing, read:

susan b. glasser on the “angry politics of now”: just about the only person who didn’t sound angry was ford, a professor and suburban mom who pronounced herself “terrified” at the outset of the hearing . . . she answered calmly, at times even clinically, as she discussed the lingering effects of the trauma and her own reluctance to come forward about it.
asked what she recalled best about an experience from which some memories were hazy or nonexistent, she replied, her voice wavering, “indelible in the hippocampus is the laughter.”
it was an extraordinary juxtaposition between ford, the scientific researcher she has become, and chrissy blasey, the shaky fifteen-year-old she was at the time she says her encounter with kavanaugh occurred.

doreen st. félix on the inevitability of kavanaugh’s confirmation:

the republicans, if they stick together, have the necessary votes. a veneer of civility made it seem as if the senators were questioning ford and #kavanaugh to get to the truth of whether kavanaugh, as a drunk teenager, attended a party where he pinned ford to a bed and sexually assaulted her, thirty-six years ago.
but that’s not what the hearing was designed to explore.
at the time of this writing, composed in the eighth hour of the grotesque historic activity happening in the capitolhill chamber, it should be as plain as day that what we witnessed was the patriarchy testing how far its politics of resentment can go. and there is no limit.
#newyorker #art #women #newyorkercover #anajuanillustration #illustration #sexualassault #illustrationmagazine #coverillustration #harrasment 
#alirezaataollahi @alirezaataollahi #علیرضاعطاءاللهی

her cover for next week’s issue draws on the testimony of #christineblaseyford, who on thursday appeared in front of the #senatejudiciarycommittee, to recount her allegation that, in 1982, she was sexually assaulted by the #supremecourt nominee #brettkavanaugh, which he has denied.
(“she speaks for the women who have no voice,” juan says.) for more coverage of the hearing, read:

susan b. glasser on the “angry politics of now”: just about the only person who didn’t sound angry was ford, a professor and suburban mom who pronounced herself “terrified” at the outset of the hearing . . . she answered calmly, at times even clinically, as she discussed the lingering effects of the trauma and her own reluctance to come forward about it.
asked what she recalled best about an experience from which some memories were hazy or nonexistent, she replied, her voice wavering, “indelible in the hippocampus is the laughter.”
it was an extraordinary juxtaposition between ford, the scientific researcher she has become, and chrissy blasey, the shaky fifteen-year-old she was at the time she says her encounter with kavanaugh occurred.

doreen st. félix on the inevitability of kavanaugh’s confirmation:

the republicans, if they stick together, have the necessary votes. a veneer of civility made it seem as if the senators were questioning ford and #kavanaugh to get to the truth of whether kavanaugh, as a drunk teenager, attended a party where he pinned ford to a bed and sexually assaulted her, thirty-six years ago.
but that’s not what the hearing was designed to explore.
at the time of this writing, composed in the eighth hour of the grotesque historic activity happening in the capitolhill chamber, it should be as plain as day that what we witnessed was the patriarchy testing how far its politics of resentment can go. and there is no limit.

text_retweet:
we end our long run of #piabadasswomen with this inspiring video from @jl.pottery, jill leary, who participated in the challenge. to me, this video represents the strength and perseverance of women across time and culture. it would be an oversight not to include a piabadasswomen who makes work with such confidence and surety. based in carmel, ny, jill is a knitter, mom, and artist. .

a special and enormous thanks to tess mattern, @tessmattern, who stepped in to help at just the right time and whose insight and hard work were invaluable. we featured wonderful women over the past few months and know that there a million more that could have been featured. while i’m sad to let this theme go, we will revisit again in the future and going forward will simply work more women into our posts. tomorrow we return to our usual two-week themes. thanks to all of you who followed along and supported our effort to promote women and the #metoo movement in ceramics in particular. -@ayumihorie

text:
juana valdes’ hanging by is a collection of text-based ceramic tiles that break down a poetic phrase so that each tile presents the viewer with a new message. a collection of her ceramic ‘colored china rags’ approximate household rags but are made from bone china—distinguished from all other porcelain for its whiteness and translucency. in altering the clay “body” through inserting pigment directly into the clay, valdes questions skin color, tones, aging, and gender bias. her work also serves as a way of highlighting and creating the beauty within the object and artifact of labor.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
last december during miami art week, @anthony_spinello and @zoelukov curated the first in a series of alternative art fairs, entitled “fair.” fair., an alternative non-commercial art fair that took place december 7-10, 2017 at brickell city centre, served as a platform for a diverse and multigenerational group of women artists. fair. seeked to address gender inequality in the art world and beyond by providing space for radical women artists to create site-specific interventions in a non-traditional venue.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
fair. was generously supported by swire properties inc, in partnership with the john s. and james l. knight foundation.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
photo: diana larrea / @parcialmentenublada
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
#juanavaldes #genderequality #brickellcitycentre #fairmarket #fairatbcc #wearehere #spinelloprojects #knightfoundation

text:
we must decide whether to stay small, quiet 🤫 and uncomplicated - or allow ourselves to grow as big, loud and complex as we were made to be. 🍁 
i spent the first 28 years of my life trying to be small. to not draw too much attention, to keep friends, fit in. to save my complications for my myself, when my head hit the pillow at night. and you know what! i wasn’t being myself and i was bullied and betrayed by girls in middle and high school who i thought were friends anyway. so. not. worth. it. 🍁 
for 28 looooong years, i defined myself by external factors. because society does that to you. i lost friends in college bc i was an uptight premed who studied too hard (albeit those friends weren’t true ones since they didn’t uplift my dreams)...but it was hard all the same. i focused on my dream to study 📖 hard and better the world. then i got to intern year and was bullied, betrayed and belittled more than ever in my life. and you know what!!!!! it broke me. but i hatched 🐣 the long-overdue knowledge that i decide my own worth. no nasty angry overworked resident. no adult who is so unhappy with their own life that they project that out into the world. no one. i’m big. i’m loud about what matters. and i’m complicated. we all are. i want to see that respected in patient care. so i’m gonna keep working to gain the knowledge and experience to bestow confidence on other people walking 🚶‍♀️ the path of keeping small, quiet and uncomplicated. 🍁 
please be you. without apology. i promise it will be beautiful. -xo

text: suicide:  a friend and fellow artist, @sethsnowden.world, and his vulnerable post about his battle with depression recently inspired me. it reminds me of the #metoo movement and the outpouring of personal accounts that women shared, empowering themselves while educating the masses of just how real the problem is.  with mental health at the forefront of conversation after losing so many seemingly happy public figures, i feel it imperative that we all share our experiences.  social media gives the illusion that we are living our best lives.  even in person we are capable of burying the darkest parts of us in an attempt to be the person we think we need to be for others to love us. for myself, this manifests into crippling social anxiety that can come off as standoffish or shy, when on the inside all i am yearning for is sincere heartfelt connections. depression and anxiety is something i have witnessed from a young age and have battled with on and off my whole life. when i was 21, it reached a peak.  i had just quit playing college football after being yelled at for not practicing with a migraine. before this point it was my identity both socially and in my family.  i was no longer sure who i was. i knew art was my passion, but in the culture i had been subjected to i had no context as to how to apply it in a meaningful way.  my pain was best masked by partying, and filling holes with shallow relationships and sexual encounters that left me more empty than before. i never felt addicted to alcohol or drugs, but i would indulge heavily in an attempt to feel accepted.  the migraines started in eighth grade. sometimes they would be weekly. the intensity would vary, but most were completely debilitating. the pain would make me wish i was dead, leaving me hung-over for days. in an attempt to reduce my migraines i was prescribed an anti-depressant. this lead to anxiety followed by a prescription to anti-anxiety meds. this combination led to panic attacks, which led to a prescription of xanax. !!!!!!!!!!!!no 21 year old should be given a prescription to xanax so frivolously!!!!!!!!!!! 👇🏼👇🏼(continued in comments)👇🏼👇🏼
name: Danny Stephens Art

text:
‘why is uncle touching me? i don’t like this !is this part of the game? ‘, i was talking to myself while playing super mario.

i would be in class 5th or 6th. we did not have video game at our place, and every alternate weekend i would ask my mom to take me to my distant relative’s place, a well known doctor, so that i could enjoy watching him playing.

i think he noticed that i wanted to play too, and one day when i was at his place, he offered me to teach.

however, his teaching was different. i was unable to understand why was he touching me everywhere! i was busy saving the mario while he was busy pushing my not so developed brests.

it would hurt, but i was unable to understand what’s going on. he would lure me by saying that he would teach me all the tips and tricks of how to win the game.

however, all his tips were taught when no one was around us. sometimes, he would ask me to sit in his lap. i would argue saying that i am a big girl now, but then he would hold my hand forcefully and would push me towards myself.

with time, i started avoiding going to his place. whenever my mom would ask to to go there, i would make an excuse saying i am sick, or i have to study.

once his wife saw him with me. i don’t know if she noticed his behaviour, but things changed after that.
however, for me, it took years to get rid of the mental scars.

i never had the audacity to share this incident with anyone till the time he died. ‘what if no one trusts me? what if everyone hates me for this?’
it took me time to understand that i was abused, and when i shared it with my friends in college, i realized that all of us have been abused by someone they trusted. ironically, none of us dared to speak.

i just hope that this metoo movement encourages everyone who has been a target of his family member’s sick mentality, to come out and speak.

it has been a topic never been entertained much. it is a horrible reality that most of the time such incident is reported only when a child is raped, causing injury and by someone not in the family.

i hope this movement let the parents know the monsters hidden in the family.

#metoo #metoomovement #childabuse #india #abuse #sexualabuse

text:
"secret. un bien trop lourd secret. celui qui a decharné mon corps, attaqué ma chair, pourri mon âme. celui qui a donné vie à mes vices et tenté de m'insuffler un courant mortel. celui pour lequel je suis devenue vulnérable et aisément pietinable. 
secret dont chacune de tes lettres est venue constituer les barreaux d'une prison intérieure, emprisonnée car je savais ma parole liée à jamais. sous tes mains suffocantes j'ai cessé de respirer pour interrompre le temps devenu douleur intense, pour ne pas me laisser pénétrer par cette danse interdite. ce secret pourtant toujours existe, et me lie à jamais dans cette noirceur où j'ai pris tant de risques, et où je subsistais. 
les mots s'alignent et s'animent, s'allient à mon être et transforment cette souffrance en un bien triste poème. les larmes ont coulé, cela n'a rien changé. le vide m'a empli. vide de sens et de vie. reste ce flot de lettres qui se déverse. reste ce sourire qui s'esquisse lorsque mon corps flotte encore après la tempête. la douceur des vagues me berce car je déverse ce secret. ce bien trop lourd secret." #withmyheart #womenpower #wordpower #libererlaparole #dontjudge #forthefutur #femininsacre #metoo #feminism #nofear #ecritureautomatique #yogapassion #yogapractice #yogainthenature

text:
@regran_ed from @enn_mae - ......sexual harassment, sexual abuse and rape is something a lot of us women have had to live with all our lives. and it's even harder to talk about it because we live in society that shames the victims instead of the abusers.
_
i was a victim of abuse first as 5 years old, a victim of rape as a teenager, then abused by my then pastor and eventually while married to my ex.
_
i remembered while working with lg electronics as a teenager, i had a senior foreign colleague who would send me dirty messages and nudes on the company messenger, he would try everything to have me alone in his office or at a quiet place. i often walk into the office everyday so afraid, because prior to that time i had been a victim of rape by someone we considered family. 
_
and then one day he blocked me in the ladies and tried to force his way with me, i kept screaming until everyone rushed in. our korean boss, who was in his 70s back then was so furious, i was so shaken, and he held me for so long. the silly man was sacked that day and returned back to india that weekend. and it made me respect the boss and the organization till date.
_
i remembered while still married to my ex, and i'd show up at the hospital with bruises from sexual abuse often, and the doc always so sad and wondering why i wouldn't walk out. when i eventually worked out of that marriage for several other reasons, i remembered couple of people saying there isn't anything like rape or sexual abuse in marriage. i often pray that someone very dear to them would not end up in such situations. 
_
i truly hope we get to that place where we raise better men, who treat every woman with utmost love, dignity and respect. i look forward to having many more men in our society who stand up against sexual abusers and rapists, men who hold each other accountable on these things. 
_
while we learn to heal and rise above it with time, like every scar it lives on reminding us what we went through and survived. 
_
no we aren't victims, just survivors! #iammae #womanofvalue #metoo #survivor #victorsnotvictims #wearenotvictims #rapeculture #abuse #childabuse #notochildabuse - #regrann

text: i don’t know how i got here. i don’t know how i’m not dead. i gave up so many times but all i had the energy to do was stay in bed and cry and i mean sob till the pillow case was covered in wet spots from all the tears. i never thought i’d be here! i never thought i’d be able to go a few weeks without losing my shit again. the cycle that tried to break me over and over and over again. i used to think i was just unlucky, i just got a shitty deal in life and i had to live with it and stop being a little bitch about it. hopeless is a word i can relate to- suffering is a part of life i’ve learned to expect. i wasn’t motivated to be successful, or to be a good daughter or friend. i was angry, sad, and confused half the time- why am i like this? it’s genetics or something but why won’t anyone help me? i was so self-centered while being my own worst enemy all in the same breath. i couldn’t see that i had to ask for help that it wouldn’t magically be given, i wanted someone to save me. i felt so alone and abandoned when really i was always surrounded by so much love. depression and anxiety is a biatch- getting outside and being active is helpful but my bed is my safety net and outside is out of the fucking question. i used to get so much anxiety about leaving the house that it still takes me an hour just to go anywhere because i’m so used to wasting so much precious time in order to stay away from the judgement and eyes of others. being around people used to give me so much anxiety i would make plans to leave the house just to crawl back into bed defeated. i used to “sleep in” till 1 or 2 in the afternoon- most days i was never out of bed before noon. i don’t know how i got here- i go weeks without crying these days! i watch the sunrise most mornings either while paddling on the ocean or while taking in the best view on earth from my “office.” everyday i’m overwhelmed with gratitude and appreciation for what i have. i’m learning now that giving back to others is the greatest gift you can give yourself. i never want to hide from the fact that i had depression- that it ruled my world for many years. i never want to hide who i was because it has made me who i am #strongaf

text:
i just wanted to share my thoughts on the #metoo movement,which has been the talk of the town for the past few weeks here in india. for those of you who don't know,the #metoo movement is all about men and women opening up about the sexual harassments that they've been through. it was originally started by an american social activist named tarana burkhe,way back in 2006. this movement came to limelight when alyssa milano,an american actress posted a tweet about the issue and stated that the victims should also start opening up about it.talking about sexual harassments has always been a rarity in india because of the biased community that we live in. in most cases, poeple tend to be emotionally destroyed. they are always used to having the thought of being disrespected by the society for accepting that they had been sexually abused. as the issue is stretched further and further with more complaints coming in,i wanted to share my opinion in the public forum. just think about the impact that this movement has on the society. with the help of social media, a lot of people have got to know the sad reality,which was not possible back in the day. what we have to do is to keep supporting this movement or any such revolutionary act because that creates a lot of awareness among people. all of us are aware of the injustice that has been happening to the women in india. all of us are aware of the fact that there are women being raped every single day in the country.all of us are aware of the fact that sexual abuses are both common to men and women as well. people of all age groups are targeted. keeping all this in mind, it is our duty to make sure that a lot of awareness is created in the society. raise your voices against sexual harassments. don't just hope for the change,be the change.!!
#metoo #standagainstrape #india #chinmayi #raiseyourvoices #wordsbyken

text:
i met @taranajaneen and had the pleasure of hearing her speak at usc's @rossierjustice conference yesterday-- she's brilliant and has a powerful testimony! one thing she said that resonated with me is that when #metoo was put online via myspace in 2006, many women asked if she could lead sessions for adult groups. me too was designed for middle school girls, so tarana began thinking about how she would design curriculum for adults. she soon realized that she didn't really need to change anything because women who had been concealing their me too stories for decades were essentially in the same emotional and mental space as the 12 year old girls that tarana worked with. these women needed the same love and support as the girls. 
i feel that the same is true for all adults who experienced trauma in childhood, but never received love and support to help them process their pain. we have a lot of hurt children who are hiding in adult bodies, trying to protect themselves, and don't realize that keeping the pain and shame inside is causing further harm. we need more safe spaces for people to share, process and heal from their pain.

#pain #trauma #healing #mentalhealth

text:
eroc is 1 of 276 organizations coming together behind this call for change. join us ➡️ seekabetterworld.org | #metoo #dearworld
.
.
image description: four graphics with red backgrounds and white text. 
1) 100 school districts: we call on 100 school districts across the country to implement comprehensive sexual health education, to make a public commitment to institute protections for all young people beyond the protections of title ix, and to codify options for survivor-centered and trauma-informed restorative justice in schools.

2) federal and international policy reform: lawmakers must advance comprehensive reform to address sexual violence in its many forms, legal protections must ensure that all work is safe work, and governments must also prioritize investing in programs and services to enable survivor healing and support.

3) 20 states by 2020: by 2020, 20 states must pass laws to strengthen legal protections against sexual violence and other forms of sexual harassment at work, in communities, and every place where it occurs.

4) $300 million for healing and justice: we challenge philanthropy - including foundations, corporate donors, and individuals - to seed $300 million in u.s. funding in the next 12 months, dedicated to investing in people and organizations that are addressing sexual violence and other forms of sexual harassment throughout our culture.

text:
former president #barackobama made a thinly veiled jab at #donaldtrump on friday evening, saying it was wrong to use a position of power for attacking others as "enemies of the people and then suddenly pretending that you're concerned about civility".
.
"i would like to think that everybody in america would think it's wrong to spend all your time from a position of power vilifying people, questioning their patriotism, calling them enemies of the people and then suddenly pretending that you're concerned about civility," he told a cheering crowd.
.
trump has repeatedly called the media "fake news" and "the enemy of the people." following the discovery of multiple packages sent to people whom the president has spoken against as political enemies, as well as a suspicious package in cnn's new york bureau at the time warner center on wednesday, trump tweetedthursday that "a very big part of the anger we see today in our society is caused by the purposely false and inaccurate reporting of the mainstream media that i refer to as fake news.".
.
obama said friday, "it shouldn't be democratic or republican to say you don't try to punish political opponents or threaten the freedom of the press just because you don't like what they say.".
.
#impeachtrump

text:
(thank you @thenewpress for this copy of) tough cases: judges tell the stories of some of the hardest decisions they've ever made // canan, mize, & weisberg
〰
"the strength of a legal system is better gauged by the attention we pay to the losing party and by the respect for judicial process that such attention may engender." [robert h. alsdorf]
〰
ever since #kavanaugh was confirmed for the supreme court, i have lost so much more trust in our legal system. this book, a collection of essays from judges across the country about their hardest cases, gave me hope & frustration in equal measures. hope, because i read many judges detail the care with which they interpret the law & seek to do right by the courts, not their own politics or the whims of the people. frustration, because, again, i do not inherently trust the law as a guidepost for the rights of the people.
〰
i do think this book helped me understand a bit more the ins & outs of the legal system. and my heart sang reading the essay by allie greenleaf maldonado, chief judge of the little traverse bay bands of odawa indians. this was the first i'd read of tribal justice, which is more restorative than punitive, based in the belief that "no matter what has been done to our people to dirty them or what they have done to themselves, they have the power to transform their lives." imagine if our country's justice system sought to restore & transform, not to lock away & punish. we have so much to fight for.

text:
(✰✰✰) em 1978, john carpenter, através do filme "halloween - o regresso do mal", pariu michael myers, o serial killer de máscara inexpressiva, com especial apetite por babysitters (mais especificamente a laurie strode - eternizada pela jamie lee curtis -, embora não colocasse de parte qualquer outro naco de carne humano suburbano), que personificava a encarnação  do mal no seu estado mais básico. 
o "coisa" franchisingou-se (para além de ter dado origem per si a um novo  subgénero cinematográfico no universo do terror, ao qual se lhe foram juntando "clones" e "primos afastados"), e ao que parece ainda não entrou na crise da meia-idade. de facto, 40 anos volvidos, o ícone retorna (pela décima vez) para atazanar o "dia das bruxas", desta feita sob a tutela de david gordon green (com uma mãozinha do próprio john carpenter enquanto produtor executivo e compositor).
fá-lo ignorando toda a "tralha" que se seguiu ao produto original, fazendo tábua rasa das respectivas sequelas e prequelas (e consequentemente das evoluções que os personagens base e a narrativa foram sofrendo ao longo do tempo), assumindo-se como uma ligação directa ao "1° episódio da saga". e para dar consistência a tal intento até foi buscar os dois protagonistas iniciais para um derradeiro choque de titãs. 
o bad boy (que consegue fugir do hospital-prisão, no qual esteve internado durante 40 anos sem emitir uma só palavra) não julgue que vai ter tarefa fácil, já que a vítima (quiçá inspirada pelo #metoo) tranformou-se, igualmente, numa "predadora" sedenta de vingança.
esta transfiguração da personagem feminina revela-se o grande foco de interesse desta revisitação, pena que depois não seja devidamente "desenvolvida" (tal como a nova relação de forças entre ambos), já que a meio da película se involui, de modo atabalhoado, para o básico/característico "corre, mata, persegue, foge" ... ainda mais, sem provocar "sustos por aí além" (simples gore light). ainda assim, cumpre com eficácia a função de "mera distração".
#halloween #johncarpenter #davidgordongreen #terrormovies #instamovies #cinemacomcritica #cinemamagic #cinematic #cinemaximum #cinemax #cinematography #bestfilm #cinemalovers #cinephile

text: channeling that divine feminine this rainy weekend.  with the state of this world... it can be hard to be a woman of color in "trump's america". but i must remember that as the last bit of toxic patriarchal/ white supremacist/fascism spews its hate speech and trauma laced violence... we too are brewing in self-love, white light powered, divine feminine excellence.  and we get to remember every day that the future is female.  and that the #metoo movement was only the beginning to something that is taking major hold in this country/society/cultural identity.  no fear my dear ones.  goddess is with us.  and our collective light will defeat this darkness.  #thefutureisfemale #manifestingmagic #magicalmaxali #divinefeminine #feminist #equalrights #humanrights

বর্তমানে বলিউড ইন্ডাস্ট্রির আতঙ্কের নাম #মিটু আন্দোলন। প্রায় প্রতিদিনই ভারতীয় গণমাধ্যমের খবরের শিরোনাম হচ্ছে এই ইস্যুটি। তাই এ আন্দোলনকে গুরুত্বের সঙ্গে নিয়েছে বলিউড ইন্ডাস্ট্রি। ভারতীয় গণমাধ্যমের সূত্রে জানা যায়, সম্প্রতি বলিউড ইন্ডাস্ট্রির নানান সঙ্কট নিয়ে দেশটির প্রধানমন্ত্রী নরেন্দ্র মোদির কাছে গিয়েছিলেন বলিউডের সাতজন প্রতিনিধি। ওই প্রতিনিধি দলে ছিলেন অভিনেতা, পরিচালক ও প্রযোজক। তাদের মধ্যে ছিলেন আমির খান, রাজ কুমার হিরানি, আনন্দ এল রায়, সিদ্ধার্থ রায় কাপুরসহ অনেকেই। তারা বলিউড ইন্ডাস্ট্রির দুরবস্থা এবং #মিটু নিয়ে আলোচনা করেছেন।

ভারতে সিনেমা হলের সংখ্যা বাড়ানো প্রসঙ্গেও তারা কথা বলেন। বলিউডের এই সমস্ত সঙ্কটে মোদির সাহায্য চেয়েছেন প্রতিনিধিরা। তবে এই প্রতিনিধি দলে কোনো নারী সদস্য না থাকায় অনেকেই সমালোচনা করছেন নেট দুনিয়ায়। তাদের মতে এই প্রতিনিধি দলে কয়েকজন নারী সদস্য থাকতে পারত।

যদিওই মোদির সঙ্গে বলিউড প্রতিনিধি দলের এই সাক্ষাৎ বিষয়ে আনুষ্ঠানিক কোনো ঘোষণা বা ব্যাখ্যা পাওয়া যায়নি প্রতিনিধি দলের কাছ থেকে। #metoo

text:
this creative mind is lynn nottage, columbia university’s professor of playwriting and two time pulitzer prize winner for drama (that’s right, two times)! she is the first and only woman to have achieved this award twice (2009, 2017) paving the way for future female pulitzer prize winners. nottage attended brown university and yale school of drama. she’s also earned honorary awards from julliard and albright. she’s from brooklyn, ny, and is best known for her play, intimate apparel.

photo source: chicago crusader .

this is a powerful time for learning and teaching. with mercury and jupiter being in scorpio we delve into the waters of our emotional bodies and uncover hidden things from the subconscious! this has been a very powerful wk, with the full moon conjunct uranus and the sun conjunct venus, refer to post from october 24th ;) how does this affect things externally?! well almost about a year ago exactly when jupiter went into scorpio, we learned about harvey weinstein’s misdeeds and the #metoo movement started... jupiter in scorpio is uncovering the taboo and has to do with things like sexual exploitation. there could be a feeling collectively of learning too much information about a subject or being faced with people who are going off the deep end to communicate their beliefs in horrific ways such as the shooting we had this morning in pittsburgh and explosive devices being sent to homes of people that someone disagreed with! these are the lower vibrations of this energy and we need to be aware of that. harness this energy and use it to uncover the depths of yourself, removing any blockages or channeling that energy in positive ways to educate others and follow your dharma✨ come on and work it out with me today⚡️

it is fun being sexual
but only when it's consensual.
the lines are blurred & grey
so boy you better learn to navigate.
.
.
in the event that you're confused about consent, know that implication is different from intent.
not a no, not a maybe, boy you need a yes,
otherwise it won't be considered consent.
did she join you for a drink, & down a glass of gin,
in the state of disorient, she cannot consent.
did she agree before? baby that's a closed door
you need to ask again, otherwise it's not consent.

text:
i was so excited to be invited to stand with 20 other diverse and gorgeous women for this project!! and the adventure has only just begun... .
this last year has been transformational for me -- being a part of this collective of women who showed up authentically, courageously, and together as sisters, to tell the truth about our journey to freedom (through stories and gorgeous photography). .
during this pivotal time in history, with the #metoo movement and the political climate -- creating space and holding space for one another to be heard and to be free is what we're called to do. . 
stand with your sisters. join us in nyc for our kindle release event of a movement we can be proud of. . 
eventbrite limited tickets: link in @freedomandfeminism bio .

pre_proc_tweet:
pujolicuous!! red and white are two authentic puja colors.. somehow they do bring out the best in you during the festivals. it was kojagori lokkhi pujo and i wore this red soft khadi  in jacquard pattern with weaved sequins and large pompoms. this is from the loved mrapaliboutique.

and with this stas the wait for diwali ❤️❤️ this is also my entry for the selfie queen challenge by aree.man
. selfie is all about self love. self love is very misunderstood term. as i have mentioned in many of my earlier posts that it is most impoant to accept and love self as that gives you the way to accept and love others as they are. as you do not wanna change you will not want to change others too. the more you understand yourself and your needs the more you grow and  understand others. it is never right or wrong it is always situations. with  campaign going on we all know how impoant it is that we speak for ourselves. as women we are taught to be selfless and we contradict ourselves the most by not showing some love to our own wishes. we should be selfless, self dependent and do what we want sometimes too because we are not dependent on anyone for love we have immense positivity in ourselves . we can find peace in ourselves  too. selfie is capturing your moments with  yourself. i have travelled alone quite a few times and selfies are the way to capture those beautiful pictures and enjoy.

most of my posts have the first picture as my selfie or at least one selfie for sure because in morning while i leave for work there is no one and thats when u look fresh, so u end up taking a selfie. and to be honest i feel i know from which angle i will look better 😜🙈🙊 tagging the selfie queens in my life  selfies)
 selfies)
 (visit her page and u would know)
 (she is the queen of selfies)
 (she takes all her videos by herself)

text:
ok peeps, it is here!!💃🏼💃🏼💃🏼
.
i could not be more excited about launching my signature program - the inner presence mastermind! i’ve spent months organizing this and years learning what i’m about to share. 😱
.
this program is legit full of everything i have used to transform my life. i studied with gurus and healers in india, yogis in bali, and learned from countless coaches and experts around the world. i’ve combined literally everything i know about overcoming your past (including grief, sexual assault, trauma) and your mind (aka fear, doubts, anxiety, insecurities, limiting beliefs... you name it!).
.
in the first month you’ll learn how to release all the old baggage that is holding you back or keeping you stuck in sh*tty patterns. (this is a game changer. until you totally release the past it will keep coming back to haunt ya 👻). once you’re free of that, it’s so much easier to step confidently into who you truly are - which is what i’ll help you do in the second month. i’m sharing all the tips and tools on how i overcame my insecurities and negative thoughts in order to fully love myself. finally, once we’ve got ya feeling so in love with yourself, you are going to be not only happier but also aligned and ready to start achieving your dreams - which is month 3! this is manifestation 101, connecting to your intuition, and creating abundance in all aspects of the word! ✨✨
.
seriously - this program is the foundation that you need in order to start having the life, career, and relationships that you desire. 🙌🏽
.
so if you’re tired of carrying all that baggage; ready to kick old patterns to the curb, or ready to finally be 100% confident and in love with yourself - check out the link in my bio!
.
the mastermind starts in just over a week and there are limited spots available! register by oct 31 and you’ll get an earlybird bonus which is a total game changer! and this is all at a beta price which won’t happen again!
.
you deserve to start living the life of your dreams right now. no more waiting... no more hoping things will change. it’s up to you - take control of your life and invest in yourself today!! you won’t regret it 🙏🏼💕

text:
#roundbooxnews
in the past one month, indian film industry has witnessed a number of veterans as well as struggling actresses confessing their stories of harrasments and sexual assaults.
reputed actors and directors have been accused of sexual misconducts and assaults. 
#metoo movement has spread its roots in various industries throughout the country, irrespective of the level of operation or category. film industry, private offices, and even college associations have found themselves being chased by the movement.

despite innumerate confessions, very few numbers of significant actions have been taken. it takes a lot of courage to come out and acknowledge one's trauma. however, women need to understand that claims should come earliest for taking considerable action against the assaulters.

the question arises, what's taking women years to come out and speak up about their experiences?
lack of people who are concerned. 
are we really listening to their experiences?
are we taking appropriate actions against the assaulters?

#metoo is not just a moment. it's a revolution that should have introduced in india years ago and now, #timesup

#roundboox #metoo #metoocampaign #metooindia  #timesup #timesupmovement #bollywood

1) covenantal relationship with god: re most vulnerable 
2) critical engagement with topic textually and otherwise does not weaken community; strengthens it.
3) secrecy kills, transparency opens up ways we train clergy, hold them accountable and keeps traditions alive 
4) women as whole, not merely vesselized

text:
if my life were a silent movie, would you see my voice? 
or believe it wasn't there.
would you in fact be as blind to my skill as you are deaf to my choice? 
i would portray the damsel with a hero's presence and unlikable face. 
i would be obscured until you blew off the dust a century later and laid your eyes upon my silver gown made of lace.
the years of being invisible would give me a song to sing.
only then would you hear,
only then you would listen.
and bow your head in silent shame.
i will be more than just an image,
i will be one to fear.
one to revere.
i will not just be one and the same.
i will be me.
i will be free,
and you?
you will be mute.
.
.
.
✴♾✴♾✴♾✴♾✴♾✴♾✴♾✴♾✴♾✴♾✴
.
.
.

text:
the fawcett society recently published a briefing on what's changed in the wake of the #metoo movement. they found that #metoo and the events of the last year have challenged people to change their thinking about sexual harassment. 38% of people in the uk agree that they had thought differently about what behaviour is and isn’t acceptable over the last year – and 31% of people have had a conversation with someone of the opposite sex about sexual harassment.

they also found that over half of women aged 18-34 and 58% of young men say they have been more willing challenge behaviour or comments they think are unacceptable. do you agree with their findings?

text:
this got me crying😢😢 we ve all got a story to tell. kindly support this movement if you are in lagos and ogun. i will be there for ibadan. lets help a child@regrann from @thehealedwomanfoundation -  the thought was to wait till next year to start our projects as a foundation. but there are women and girls who have been suffering from abuses and the effects hoping for a glimpse of hope and someone who at least understands and will believe them. waiting would mean leaving them to hurt till next year...no.
.
.
with our project, rescue the girl child, we will be visiting primary and secondary schools all over nigeria to educate female students about sexual abuse, child trafficking and other forms of abuse that can affect them. with this, we want to get to meet girls who are victims and offer them help in the form of counseling and by partnering with other organizations, get them legal help too.
.
.
our first tour will be next month, november 2018. our target is 20 schools within lagos and ogun states.
.
.
rescue the girl child tour needs partnership (most important), volunteering and donations to take it further. our target is to reach out to girls in all schools in nigeria.
.
.
to partner with us, volunteer, or make a donation, send an email to admin@thehealedwoman.org or call +2347069403717
.
.
cac/it/no 118484

text: do you have a plan for keeping your child safe when you have overnight guests? many parents assume that friends and family are trustworthy so they welcome them into their home for overnight stays without even considering the fact that their guest might be a predator. therefore, we encourage parents to have a plan when it comes to overnight guests. depending on the age of your child, you may want to have your child sleep in your room during this time, or at the very least use a monitoring device in their room. for older kids, you might want to have them leave their door open and have a talk with them about what to do if the guests enters their room uninvited. you should also leave your door open at night so you can hear any movement in the house. these may seem like extremes, but having a plan to keep your child safe may be the difference between a predator attempting to abuse your child and them realizing they don't have the access they need to carry out their plan. #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #sexcrimes #rapevictims #rape #victims #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate

text:
shame : a painful feeling of humiliation or distress caused by the consciousness of wrong or foolish behaviour.

i read with dismay as account after account of young professionals in the arts tumble out in the #metoo deluge. i know some stories similar to these and when i heard them, perhaps shrugged them off as normal ... ‘after all it happens’ sort of event. perhaps not. i feel perhaps i should’ve gone looking for these people and offered support. so if you are young (or not!) and want to talk, 🙋🏽‍♀️i’m available, in confidence and for what it’s worth!

i think it’s time we all reached out a bit and looked out for the younger women. send me a message if you want to talk, need advice or help.
#abouttime #metooindia #youarenotalone 
pic: lajja gauri the female goddess associated with fertility, prosperity and divinity. holds lotus stalks and i’ve never found an explanation that quite explains why she’s called lajja ( another word that’s not quite literally shame)
to me she’s just a celebration of all that’s female and powerful and worthy of reverence. as is every woman out there... call, message, reach out!
